title: Cosmic33
items.summary: In a future world devastated by disease, a convict is sent back in time to gather information about the man-made virus that wiped out most of the human population on the planet.
items.tagline: The future is history.
items.title: 12 Monkeys

items.summary: 97 years after a nuclear war, human kind is living in space. 100 juvenile delinquents are sent down to Earth to see if the planet is habitable.
items.title: Pilot

items.summary: Discovering that Jasper may still be alive, Clarke, Bellamy, Finn, Wells and Murphy head out to find him. On the Ark, Abby is determined to prove Earth is habitable, and enlists a mechanic to craft an escape pod.
items.title: Earth Skills

items.summary: As a dangerous, acidic fog approaches, Clarke, Finn and Wells set out in search of a seaweed-like plant to make an antibiotic poultice for Jasper's wounds, while a vulnerable young girl follows when Bellamy takes a group out hunting for food.
items.title: Earth Kills

items.summary: Bellamy, Clarke and Finn try to protect Charlotte when everyone learns she killed Wells. On the Ark, Abby risks getting floated in order to give Raven the chance to launch the escape pod.
items.title: Murphy's Law

items.summary: A plan to contact the Ark is put in motion after Raven crash lands on Earth. Meanwhile, Abby exposes Kane's plan to reduce the population of the Ark.
items.title: Twilight's Last Gleaming

items.summary: Bellamy, Finn and Jasper head into Grounder territory to search for Octavia, as flashbacks show the siblings' difficult childhood on the Ark. Meanwhile, Raven finds out about Clarke and Finn.
items.title: His Sister's Keeper

items.summary: While Bellamy tortures the Grounder, Raven and Clarke make contact with the Ark and ask Abby to help them save Finn. On the Ark, Kane deals with his guilt, and Jaha surprises the council with a shocking revelation.
items.title: Contents Under Pressure

items.summary: Shumway secretly orders one of the 100 to kill Bellamy. Meanwhile, hallucinogenic nuts provide Octavia with an opportunity to help the Grounder escape the camp, and Bellamy and Clarke investigate a nearby underground depot, where they find military weapons.
items.title: Day Trip

items.summary: Finn arranges a meeting with Clarke and the leader of the Grounders in order to bring peace, however a sceptical Clarke warns Bellamy, who along with Jasper and Raven follow them to the meeting with weapons. On the Ark, Diana takes over the exodus ship.
items.title: Unity Day

items.summary: Murphy returns to the camp carrying a horrific virus created by the Grounders to weaken the camp. After learning the Grounders plan to attack the next day, Bellamy, Finn and Raven come up with a plan to delay them.
items.title: I Am Become Death

items.summary: Clarke and Finn are captured by Anya, who forces them to save the life of a victim of the explosion. Meanwhile, Raven deals with her split from Finn, and Kane fights to save the Ark and it's survivors.
items.title: The Calm

items.summary: Clarke and Finn come face to face with a new enemy after Lincoln rescues them from Anya, while Bellamy, Raven, Octavia and Jasper deal with a vengeful Murphy. On the Ark, Jaha makes a plan to try and get to Earth.
items.title: We Are Grounders (1)

items.summary: As the remaining members of the 100 face off against the Grounders, Jaha makes a noble sacrifice to ensure the Ark makes it to Earth.
items.title: We Are Grounders (2)

items.summary: Clarke is still on her own in the white room, frantically attempting to make sense of her bizarre surroundings. Lincoln and Octavia's plan is ruined and an enemy returns.
items.title: The 48

items.summary: Clarke wants answers from the President. Abby performs emergency surgery. Octavia will do anything to find Lincoln.
items.title: Inclement Weather

items.summary: After discovering a horrifying project in Mount Weather's medical ward, Clarke joins forces with an unexpected ally.
items.title: Reapercussions

items.summary: Clarke ends up being betrayed by somebody that she trusted. Bellamy, Finn and Murphy attempt to save a stranger.
items.title: Many Happy Returns

items.summary: Kane takes part in a mission to make peace with the Grounders. Jasper decides to take part in a risky experiment. Lincoln enters a world of pain and President Dante Wallace issues a warning.
items.title: Human Trials

items.summary: Tensions are running high between Clarke and Finn. Raven finds out that Mount Weather is interfering with their communication systems.
items.title: Fog of War

items.summary: Bellamy is able to get Clarke to agree to accompany him to the drop ship. Dr. Tsing is in charge of a deadly experiment.
items.title: Long Into an Abyss

items.summary: Clarke comes back to Camp Jaha with some shocking news. Finn has to face the consequences of his actions.
items.title: Spacewalker

items.summary: Lexa and Clarke manage to make a deal.The newly created alliance is under threat. Monty comes up with a plan.
items.title: Remember Me

items.summary: Lives are left in danger following the arrival of a new threat. Lincoln and Bellamy decide to break into Mount Weather.
items.title: Survival of the Fittest

items.summary: Lincoln and Bellamy's efforts to get into Mount Weather has some brutal consequences.
items.title: Coup de Grâce

items.summary: Clarke is faced with a difficult choice and Raven helps Bellamy navigate Mount Weather as Dr. Tsing begins to harvest the 47, while Jaha and Murphy encounter a stranger on their journey to the City of Light.
items.title: Rubicon

items.summary: Clarke begins to question Lexa's leadership decisions and Indra continues to push Octavia. Meanwhile, at Mount Weather, Jasper steps up into the role of leader, and Cage throws Maya into a life threatening situation.
items.title: Resurrection

items.summary: Lexa and Clarke get into a heated discussion during battle preparations; Bellamy races against time.
items.title: Bodyguard of Lies

items.summary: Wick and Raven are faced with a setback. Maya and Jasper witness a terrible act.
items.title: Blood Must Have Blood (1)

items.summary: Jaha makes a surprising move. Clarke gets help from an unexpected source. Lincoln seeks revenge.
items.title: Blood Must Have Blood (2)

items.summary: Three months have passed since the tragedy at Mount Weather and our heroes learn that a bounty has been put on Clarke’s head. Unbeknownst to Clarke, a team led by Bellamy and Kane journeys deep into Grounder territory to save her. Meanwhile, Murphy finds his way to the mansion and discovers a very different Jaha on a very different mission.
items.title: Wanheda (1)

items.summary: Bellamy and Kane risk life and limb to rescue Clarke. In an attempt to avoid worrying about her daughter, Abby focuses on whether to open Mount Weather as a medical facility. Meanwhile, Murphy plots to betray his former Chancellor.
items.title: Wanheda (2)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The 100/S 03/The 100 S03E03 Ye Who Enter Here.mkv
items.summary: Clarke wrestles with a decision. Bellamy learns that something isn't what it seems. Meanwhile, Murphy plots to betray his former Chancellor.
items.title: Ye Who Enter Here

items.summary: Clarke discovers the mastermind behind a devious plan. Kane struggles to keep the peace. Meanwhile, Jasper’s grief drives him to reckless behavior.
items.title: Watch the Thrones

items.summary: Pike's twisted crusade threatens Clarke's attempts for peace. Raven becomes a target, while Murphy tries to conspire against Jaha.
items.title: Hakeldama

items.summary: Clarke is torn between vengeance and mercy. Meanwhile, Kane and Octavia work together to avert a disaster, and Abby continues to worry about Raven.
items.title: Bitter Harvest

items.summary: Lexa tries to maintain peace and order within the clans, and Clarke uncovers a strange and game-changing truth. Meanwhile, a flashback takes us into the darker chapter of humanity’s past.
items.title: Thirteen

items.summary: Kane is searching for a peaceful way to handle things but soon realizes he may be forced to resort to drastic measures. Meanwhile, Pike suspects that there may be a leak within the walls of Arkadia. Lastly, Raven has a plan and reaches out to Jasper for help.
items.title: Terms and Conditions

items.summary: Clarke discovers a shocking truth, and Octavia is forced to make a decision that could have devastating consequences. Meanwhile, Kane and Abby share a moment.
items.title: Stealing Fire

items.summary: Jaha employs a terrifying new method to convince Abby to join his cause, Kane is on a mission, and Bellamy is hit with a hard truth. Meanwhile, Monty finds himself in a precarious situation, and Jasper rushes to save one of his own.
items.title: Fallen

items.summary: Alie forces Raven’s dark side to come out, and Jasper’s anger continues to grow. Meanwhile, Octavia wrestles with her place in the world, and Monty is forced to make a split second decision.
items.title: Nevermore

items.summary: Jaha returns to Polis, and Murphy has a surprise encounter. Meanwhile, Octavia uncovers a clue.
items.title: Demons

items.summary: Clarke is on a mission that could change everything. Meanwhile, Murphy gains insight that might prove useful in ensuring his survival. Lastly, Kane reaches a breaking point.
items.title: Join or Die

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The 100/S 03/The 100 S03E14 Red Sky at Morning.mkv
items.summary: Clarke, Bellamy, Octavia and Jasper hit a tragic roadblock. Meanwhile, Raven and Monty make an important discovery.
items.title: Red Sky at Morning

items.summary: Clarke finds hope in the most unlikely place. Meanwhile, Alie’s master plan comes together.
items.title: Perverse Instantiation (1)

items.summary: Our heroes begin to face the reality of their tragic situation. Everyone prepares for a final showdown.
items.title: Perverse Instantiation (2)

items.summary: Clarke and her friends struggle with how to proceed after the fate of the world is revealed.
items.title: Echoes

items.summary: The burden of leading weighs heavily upon Clarke and Bellamy when different challenges force them to determine who will live and die.
items.title: Heavy Lies the Crown

items.summary: Jaha leads Clarke and Bellamy down a road to possible salvation while tensions rise in Arkadia and Polis.
items.title: The Four Horsemen

items.summary: Continued struggles with leadership and trust in Arkadia and Polis take violent turns while Abby leads a team to a distant location hoping to find answers.
items.title: A Lie Guarded

items.summary: Clarke makes a desperate plea with a former allied force in an attempt to avoid a war and ensure the survival of her people.
items.title: The Tinder Box

items.summary: Clarke and Roan are forced to work together when they are tasked to deliver a dangerous but crucial asset to Abby through enemy territories.
items.title: We Will Rise

items.summary: Clarke's arrival on the island quickly takes a turn for the worse. Meanwhile, Bellamy tries to avoid further tragedy in Arkadia.
items.title: Gimme Shelter

items.summary: After a disappointing discovery, Clarke and Abby question how far they're willing to go. Meanwhile, Jaha finds a lead to the mysterious Second Dawn.
items.title: God Complex

items.summary: Jasper and Bellamy go on a quest. Meanwhile, Clarke struggles to keep the peace after word of Jaha's discovery spreads.
items.title: DNR

items.summary: Octavia fights in the final battle for her people's survival, but not everyone is willing to play fair.
items.title: Die All, Die Merrily

items.summary: Clarke faces the consequences of her fateful choice.
items.title: The Other Side

items.summary: Jaha and Kane disagree over how to handle their grim reality. Meanwhile, Clarke leads a group to save a friend.
items.title: The Chosen

items.summary: It's a race against the end of the world as Praimfaya arrives forcing our heroes to make impossible decisions to ensure their survival.
items.title: Praimfaya

items.summary: Clarke struggles to survive on a desolate, scorched earth while her friends in space come across a long-awaited beacon of hope.
items.title: Eden

items.summary: Octavia is forced to take guidance from an unlikely ally when the future of the bunker and all those inside it is jeopardized.
items.title: Red Queen

items.summary: Bellamy leads the charge investigating a potential way home. Meanwhile, Clarke and Madi deal with the new, uncertain threat to their home.
items.title: Sleeping Giants

items.summary: Our Heroes are forced to rely on the help of Shallow Valley's dangerous new inhabitants in order to save some of their own, with surprising results.
items.title: Pandora's Box

items.summary: Octavia leads her people towards Shallow Valley against the advice of Clarke and Bellamy. Meanwhile, Kane and Abby adjust to a new set of challenges.
items.title: Shifting Sands

items.summary: Kane's attempt to prove himself useful tests Wonkru's allegiance to Octavia. Madi faces an unexpected threat inside Wonkru, forcing Clarke to make an unlikely ally.
items.title: Exit Wounds

items.summary: Clarke and Bellamy make a startling discovery about Wonkru’s battle plans as Echo risks her friendship with Raven to complete her mission.
items.title: Acceptable Losses

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The 100/S 05/The 100 S05E08 How We Get to Peace.mkv
items.summary: Clarke’s determination to protect Madi puts Bellamy  in an impossible position.
items.title: How We Get to Peace

items.summary: The growing fractures in Wonkru threaten to explode once and for all. Meanwhile, in Shadow Valley, Murphy starts a fire, unleashing catastrophic results.
items.title: Sic Semper Tyrannis

items.summary: Monty strives to show Wonkru an alternative to war, and to the valley itself. Meanwhile, Abby’s health continues to deteriorate, along with McCreary’s patience.
items.title: The Warriors Will

items.summary: As Clarke races to save Abby, she learns more about the trials and tribulations Wonkru faced in the bunker, and the impossible decisions they were forced to make in the dark year.
items.title: The Dark Year

items.summary: Octavia leads her people into war. While behind enemy lines, our heroes must overcome their differences to save Wonkru from extinction.
items.title: Damocles (1)

items.summary: Clarke and her friends must risk everything to fight one last battle for survival, only to glimpse an even darker threat to the last living valley on Earth.
items.title: Damocles (2)

items.summary: When the Narn attack a Centauri colony, Londo and G'Kar nearly come to blows.  Meanwhile, raiders are attacking transport ships near the station.
items.title: Midnight on the Firing Line

items.summary: A badly damaged ship is brought into the station and the strange alien inside is identified as a soul hunter - an immortal race who can sense death and supposedly steal someone's soul.
items.title: Soul Hunter

items.summary: Londo unknowingly falls for a beautiful slave, whose owner wants her to steal sensitive information. Garibaldi discovers that someone is using a restricted communications channel.
items.title: Born to the Purple

items.summary: Dr. Franklin gets a visit from an old friend and former mentor, xenoarchaeologist Dr. Vance Hendricks who wants Franklin's help to analyze some organic artifacts he found on a dead world. But the artifacts seem to have a will of their own and start to manipulate Hendricks' assistant.
items.title: Infection

items.summary: Sinclair's old flame, Catherine Sakai, arrives during a week-long festival when humans and aliens demonstrate their dominate religious beliefs.  An old enemy sends an assassin to kill G'Kar.
items.title: The Parliament of Dreams

items.summary: The Psi-Cops arrive at the station to capture a rogue telepath, Talia's old Psi Corps instructor. Catherine Sakai is warned not to survey Sigma 957 by G'Kar.
items.title: Mind War

items.summary: A racist group is terrorizing non-humans on Babylon 5. Meanwhile Londo has trouble with two young Centauri who want to break with tradition by ignoring their arranged marriages, and instead marry for love.
items.title: The War Prayer

items.summary: Sinclair is kidnapped and interrogated by two men determined to prove he betrayed earth during the Battle of the Line.
items.title: And the Sky Full of Stars
items.titleSort: And the Sky Full of Stars

items.summary: Na'Toth attacks an alien woman that has just arrived on the station, claiming that she is the Dilgar war criminal Jha'dur - known as Deathwalker. Meanwhile, Talia is hired by Kosh to oversee some rather strange negotiations.
items.title: Deathwalker

items.summary: An alien couple comes to Dr. Franklin with their fatally ill son. The child could be cured by a simple operation, but the parents' religion specifically forbids it. Meanwhile, Ivanova escorts a damaged star liner through raider territory.
items.title: Believers

items.summary: There is an explosion in one of the fighter bays just days before the president is to visit Babylon 5. A dying man implicates Garibaldi, which is just what the head of presidential security wants to hear, as she blames him for her father's death.
items.title: Survivors

items.summary: The station's dock workers stage an illegal strike after an accident in the docking bays.  G'Kar tries to take part in a Narn religious ceremony, but must find a replacement G'Quan-Eth plant that was destroyed in the accident.
items.title: By Any Means Necessary

items.summary: A Centauri noble comes to Babylon 5 to transport an important relic in Londo's possession back to the homeworld. And a mysterious man visits all the alien ambassadors asking them an unusual question.
items.title: Signs and Portents

items.summary: Garibaldi is surprised when an old friend comes to Babylon 5 to fight in the "Mutai" - a savage alien fighting arena. Meanwhile, Ivanova has trouble dealing with her father's death.
items.title: TKO

items.summary: A man comes to Babylon 5 asking the alien ambassadors for information that can help him with his quest to find the Holy Grail, while a Downbelow gangster gives security problems by mind-wiping all who oppose him.
items.title: Grail

items.summary: Sinclair's decisions the last year catch up with him, when an internal affairs investigator arrives to test the crew's loyalty to Earth Force with the help of a telepath. And Lennier shows great interest in Garibaldi's attempt at assembling a 1990's motorcycle.
items.title: Eyes

items.summary: A Minbari war cruiser comes to Babylon 5 to display the body of a recently dead Minbari leader, while Ivanova and Talia battle for the fate of a young girl with newly discovered telepathic powers.
items.title: Legacies

items.summary: Strange signals start coming from Epsilon 3, the planet below Babylon 5. A science ship is sent to investigate, but is fired upon by a defense system on the planet. Meanwhile, Garibaldi worries about a lover he left back on Mars, when fighting breaks out there.
items.title: A Voice in the Wilderness (1)

items.summary: The situation heats up when an Earth Force heavy cruiser arrives to "protect Earth's interests", and the fusion reactors on Epsilon 3 start going out of control, and may blow up the planet and Babylon 5.
items.title: A Voice in the Wilderness (2)

items.summary: Babylon 4 reappears at the same place it disappeared four years before, and Sinclair and Garibaldi lead an expedition to evacuate its crew. Meanwhile, Delenn is summoned by the Grey council. They inform her that they have selected a new leader - her.
items.title: Babylon Squared

items.summary: Dr. Franklin investigates an unlicensed medical practitioner in Downbelow, while Londo takes Lennier for a tour of Babylon 5's seedier locales. And in the brig, a convicted murderer waits for his sentence to be carried out - the death of personality.
items.title: The Quality of Mercy

items.summary: The Centauri are about to withdraw from a quadrant of space because the Narn are harassing them, when Londo gets an offer to take care of the problem. Meanwhile, Garibaldi tries to find out what his informant stumbled upon that got him killed.
items.title: Chrysalis

items.summary: Sheridan arrives at Babylon 5 to replace Sinclair and deal with a renegade Minbari Cruiser.
items.title: Points of Departure

items.summary: Sheridan's sister comes to visit him at his new command, G'Kar returns with grave tidings from the rim of known space, Dr. Franklin tries to wake Gribaldi from the coma with the alien healing device obtained from Dr. Rosen, and something is happening in Delenn's quarters.
items.title: Revelations

items.summary: A mysterious group known as "techno-mages" take up temporary residence at Babylon 5 and Londo is very eager to get an audience with them. Meanwhile, the Drazi cause problems for the newly promoted Commander Ivanova with their rather unusual election process.
items.title: The Geometry of Shadows

items.summary: A giant explorer class ship comes to Babylon 5 for re-supply - its captain an old friend of Sheridan. Dr. Franklin gets on the command staff's nerves when he starts handing out "food plans".
items.title: A Distant Star

items.summary: A 100-year-old space exploration ship appears near Babylon 5 with two passengers - a woman in cryogenic sleep, the corpse of her husband, and something sinister that has unfinished business with a half mad lurker.
items.title: The Long Dark

items.summary: A friend of Talia comes to Babylon 5 to negotiate a deal to help Mars become more self-sufficient, when a man calling out "Free Mars!" electrocutes him.
items.title: Spider in the Web

items.summary: Londo summons his three wives to Babylon 5 so he can divorce two of them, Talia gets a visit from her obnoxious ex-husband - the only man ever to leave the PSI Corps, and Delenn has her first bad hair day.
items.title: Soul Mates

items.summary: Bester returns to Babylon 5 to shut down an underground organization that smuggles rogue telepaths out of the PSI Corps' reach. Meanwhile, Sheridan has some disagreements with Earth Force over the rent of his quarters.
items.title: A Race Through Dark Places

items.summary: The aging Centauri emperor travels to Babylon 5 despite his failing health. Refa sees this as an opportunity to have Londo publicly embarrass the emperor, while G'Kar prepares to assassinate him.
items.title: The Coming of Shadows

items.summary: Babylon 5 gets considerable space problems when 25,000 Earth Force soldiers arrive. Led by General Richard Franklin, Stephen Franklin's father, they are to use Babylon 5 as a staging point for a risky military operation.
items.title: GROPOS

items.summary: While leading a Starfury squadron to investigate the disappearance of several ships, Sheridan is captured by an alien vessel. Meanwhile, Delenn is summoned to appear before the Grey Council to discuss her recent change in appearance.
items.title: All Alone in the Night

items.summary: G'Kar struggles to control the Narns on Babylon 5 as he asks the different ambassadors for help in the war against the Centauri. Ivanova shows a representative from a new species around the station, so he may decide if humans are worthy of their presence.
items.title: Acts of Sacrifice

items.summary: The president's physician comes to Babylon 5 on the run from Earth Force special intelligence. They say he has classified information he plans to sell to alien governments, though Sheridan soon learns otherwise.
items.title: Hunter, Prey

items.summary: Sheridan is assaulted by the Minbari Lovell, and is forced to kill him in self-defense. But a Minbari who witnessed the incident claims Sheridan assaulted Lovell - and everybody knows Minbari do not lie.
items.title: There All the Honor Lies

items.summary: We see life on Babylon 5 through the eyes of ISN, supplemented by interviews, statistics and even a few commercials.
items.title: And Now for a Word

items.summary: Sheridan is shocked to learn that one of the crew of the Icarus, a science ship that exploded with his wife aboard, is alive - namely Mr. Morden. A representative of the Ministry of Peace comes to the station to recruit personnel to the Nightwatch.
items.title: In the Shadow of Z'ha'dum

items.summary: Londo gets a visit from an old friend who seeks his help after being called a traitor by the Centarum. Sheridan starts hallucinating after being attacked by a dead alien.
items.title: Knives

items.summary: A 100% fatal and 100% contagious plague is killing the Markabs. Dr. Franklin tries to find a cure, but is being opposed by the Markabs themselves, who believe the plague only affects the immoral.
items.title: Confessions and Lamentations

items.summary: Lyta Alexander returns to Babylon 5 with a message from the telepath resistance: one of the command staff is a mole for PSI Corps.
items.title: Divided Loyalties

items.summary: Draal reveals himself to Sheridan, while Refa and Londo set a plan in motion that will lead to the final defeat of the Narns.
items.title: The Long, Twilight Struggle

items.summary: Kosh summons an inquisitor to test Delenn's motives, and G'Kar tries to maintain his position as leader of Babylon 5's Narn population while organizing an underground resistance.
items.title: Comes the Inquisitor

items.summary: Two officials from the Ministry of Peace come to Babylon 5; one to deal with the Centauri's continued expansion, and the other to check on the local Nightwatch. Meanwhile, a Narn heavy cruiser seeks sanctuary while they make repairs, and Keffer continues his search for proof that Shadow ships exist.
items.title: The Fall of Night

items.summary: An Earth Force investigator comes to Babylon 5 with Lt. Keffer's last recording, asking the ambassadors if they recognize the ship in it. Meanwhile, Londo takes steps to remove himself from the Shadows, and Sheridan takes the White Star out for its first mission.
items.title: Matters of Honor

items.summary: A bomber is loose on Babylon 5; setting of bombs with seemingly no pattern. G'Kar blames the Centauri, Londo blames the Narn - and in it all, Lennier is critically injured. At the same time, a group of monks request permission to live on the station.
items.title: Convictions

items.summary: The new Centauri appointed Narn government send a replacement for G'Kar, while an alien probe threatens to destroy Babylon 5 unless it gets the answers for a series of complicated scientific questions.
items.title: A Day in the Strife

items.summary: One of the monks starts having disturbing visions and realizes that his past may not be how he remembers it. Meanwhile, Lyta causes a bit of commotion when she returns from the Vorlon homeworld.
items.title: Passing Through Gethsemane

items.summary: Delenn decides it's time to try to contact some of the first ones and enlists the help of Draal, while Babylon 5 is assigned a political officer.
items.title: Voices of Authority

items.summary: Bester comes to the station to track down a dealer of Dust - an illegal drug that gives normal people temporary telepathic powers. G'Kar is also interested in the drug. He sees it as a potential weapon against the Centauri, but first he has to test it.
items.title: Dust to Dust

items.summary: Marcus starts snooping around Downbelow when some of his contacts start behaving unusually and a lurker is found dead with a strange creature bonded to his spine. Ivanova investigates Corwin's loyalties when he receives a promotion.
items.title: Exogenesis

items.summary: An archaeologist arrives at Babylon 5 with a grave massage: a dormant Shadow ship has been found on Ganymede. It must be destroyed before it falls into the hands of President Clark.
items.title: Messages from Earth

items.summary: Clark has just declared martial law, and while Nightwatch prepare to take control of the station, Zack has to decide whose side he's on. In an exercise of bad timing, the prophetic widow of emperor Turhan finally comes to the station, granting Londo the visit he's been begging her for, for a long time.
items.title: Point of No Return

items.summary: The renegade destroyer "Alexander" arrives at Babylon 5 and Sheridan is forced to announce the station's secession from the Earth Alliance, and prepare for an attack by Clark's forces. Meanwhile, Delenn is forced to go to Minbar when the Grey Council refuses to act upon increased Shadow activity.
items.title: Severed Dreams

items.summary: Delenn prepares for a ceremony of rebirth, the station's computer goes through an interesting change, Londo "encourages" Refa to stop associating with the Shadows, and the remains of the Nightwatch on Babylon 5 plan to strike at Sheridan through Delenn.
items.title: Ceremonies of Light and Dark

items.summary: Vir returns to Babylon 5 to find that he now has a wife and that two Narns are out for his blood. Meanwhile, Ivanova investigates the activities of the mysterious Centauri Abrahamo Linconi.
items.title: Sic Transit Vir

items.summary: A mysterious man comes to Babylon 5 dressed in chainmail and armed with a sword. His name? King Arthur - Son of Uther Pendragon, come to help when he is needed most.
items.title: A Late Delivery from Avalon

items.summary: Bester comes to Babylon 5, this time seeking help against a common enemy - the Shadows. Meanwhile, G'Kar demands to be included in the War Council.
items.title: Ship of Tears

items.summary: Morden returns to secure Londo's cooperation again, Garibaldi confronts Franklin about the stims, and Kosh gives Sheridan a victory against the Shadows - but at a price.
items.title: Interludes and Examinations

items.summary: Ivanova gets a distress call from herself pleading for help as the Shadows destroy Babylon 5. It is dated eight days into the future. At the same time, on Minbar, Sinclair is given a nine-hundred-year-old letter from Valen, telling him that a drastic action must be taken to prevent that future.
items.title: War Without End (1)

items.summary: While Sheridan is unstuck in time, seeing a glimpse of a future Centauri Prime in ruins, the others continue with their plan to take Babylon 4 back in time.
items.title: War Without End (2)

items.summary: The new Vorlon ambassador arrives, Sheridan decides it's time to test just how effective telepaths are against the Shadow ships, and Franklin is on walkabout in Downbelow and falls in love with a singer.
items.title: Walkabout

items.summary: Garibaldi investigates an area where a maintenance worker disappeared and finds a whole floor that was forgotten after construction, including its rather strange inhabitants. Meanwhile, Delenn is about to take on the role of Ranger One, but Neroon swears to stop her.
items.title: Grey 17 Is Missing

items.summary: Londo forces Vir to participate in a plan to kill G'Kar. Sheridan struggles with figuring out the Shadows' tactics.
items.title: And the Rock Cried Out, No Hiding Place
items.titleSort: And the Rock Cried Out, No Hiding Place

items.summary: With the Shadows next target known, a massive counterattack is prepared. Ivanova and Marcus scout ahead in the White Star, while the fleet stands by in hyperspace. At the same time, Franklin finally has to face his problems as he lies fatally wounded in Downbelow.
items.title: Shadow Dancing

items.summary: After he has recovered from the shock of seeing her, Anna gives Sheridan an ultimatum - come to Z'ha'dum with her, or never know what happened to her there.
items.title: Z'ha'dum

items.summary: In the aftermath of the explosion on Z'ha'dum, Sheridan is presumed dead and Garibaldi is missing. Delenn struggles to keep the alliance against the Shadows together, and Londo takes up his new position on Centauri Prime as security advisor to the emperor.
items.title: The Hour of the Wolf

items.summary: On Z'ha'dum, Sheridan floats somewhere between life and death. Meanwhile, G'Kar risks imprisonment to try to find Garibaldi.
items.title: Whatever Happened to Mr. Garibaldi?

items.summary: Ivanova and Marcus take a White Star out to search for more first ones to aid in the war, while Londo tries to convince G'Kar to swallow his pride so Cartagia will find him entertaining. A mysterious spacecraft makes its way towards Babylon 5.
items.title: The Summoning

items.summary: With the Vorlons destroying whole worlds, Babylon 5 is struggling to cope with the refugees. And with one Vorlon aboard, they cannot make a move without them knowing about it, so Sheridan decides to kill him. On Centauri Prime, Cartagia explains to Londo how he will become a god when the Vorlons destroy the planet.
items.title: Falling Toward Apotheosis

items.summary: As reports that the Shadows are destroying planets too start to come in, Sheridan prepares for one final showdown with the Shadows and the Vorlons. Meanwhile on Narn, Londo makes everything ready - G'Kar's chains have been weakened and an undetectable weapon has been acquired. Tonight Cartagia must die.
items.title: The Long Night

items.summary: In the hours before the Shadows and the Vorlons meet Sheridan's alliance at Corriana 6, Ivanova and Lorien search the last of the First Ones, and Londo races back to Centauri Prime in hope of removing all Shadow influence before the Vorlon planetkiller arrives.
items.title: Into the Fire

items.summary: Bester comes to Babylon 5 with information about President Clark's plans to discredit the station. But it has a price tag attached - he wants them to go to Z'ha'dum to look for any leftover technology that might help revive his lover. Garibaldi resigns his position as security chief.
items.title: Epiphanies

items.summary: A team of ISN reporters arrives at the station wanting to do a story about Babylon 5. Sheridan refuses at first, but finally agrees on the theory that at least a small part of their side of the conflict will be shown.
items.title: The Illusion of Truth

items.summary: When her clan has doubts about her reason for taking Sheridan as a mate, Delenn is required to go to Minbar to attend "the Dreaming". Sheridan sends Marcus and Franklin to Mars to make contact with the resistance there.
items.title: Atonement

items.summary: Marcus and Franklin meet their liaison to the Mars resistance, but are greeted at gunpoint by the resistance itself. Meanwhile, Sheridan confronts Garibaldi about his attitude.
items.title: Racing Mars

items.summary: Delenn investigates attacks on ships of races allied with the Minbari, and encounters the Drakh for the first time. On Mars, Franklin rallies the resistance leaders to Sheridan's cause.
items.title: Lines of Communication

items.summary: Garibaldi gets his first assignment from his new employer - helping someone getting on and off the station without having to pass through customs. He is quite surprised at who this person is. Meanwhile, Ivanova makes preparations for the first broadcast of "The Voice of the Resistance".
items.title: Conflicts of Interest

items.summary: Sheridan hatches an eccentric plan to convince the League to accept White Star patrols on their borders, while Delenn seeks help from Neroon to end the civil war that has broken out on Minbar.
items.title: Rumors, Bargains and Lies

items.summary: The warrior caste has surrounded the religious caste's stand in the capital city on Minbar, and demand they surrender or be destroyed. Meanwhile, Bester makes Lyta an offer for her body.
items.title: Moments of Transition

items.summary: With Clark having killed 10,000 unarmed refugees, Sheridan once again mobilizes for war. The first target is Proxima 3, which is being bombed into submission. At the same time, Londo tries to get G'Kar to partake in a joint Centauri-Narn statement in support of the war against Clark.
items.title: No Surrender, No Retreat

items.summary: As Sheridan's forces continue towards Earth, Garibaldi is finally allowed to meet his employer, William Edgars, face to face on Mars, and is after telepath assisted interrogation finally told what he must do to gain Edgars' complete trust. Meanwhile, Dr. Franklin discovers that Lyta can influence the Shadow modified telepaths.
items.title: Exercise of Vital Powers

items.summary: After arranging for the arrest of Sheridan's father, Garibaldi gives his former commander the news, and urges him to come to Mars to arrange a rescue operation. But Garibaldi drugs Sheridan as soon as he gets there, and hands him over to Clark's forces. Finally, Edgars reveals his plans to Garibaldi.
items.title: The Face of the Enemy

items.summary: In a bleak room, an interrogator tries to force Sheridan to admit he was under alien influence and worked to undermine Earth.
items.title: Intersections in Real Time

items.summary: Garibaldi is barely able to convince Lyta and Franklin that his recent behavior was caused by Bester, and they organize a rescue for Sheridan. Meanwhile, Ivanova gets word that a trap has been set at the fleet's next rendezvous point by a group of completely new advanced-technology destroyers.
items.title: Between the Darkness and the Light
items.titleSort: Between the Darkness and the Light

items.summary: The only obstacle remaining between Sheridan and Earth is a fleet near Mars. With the help of the resistance, Sheridan plans to smuggle Shadow modified telepaths onto the fleet, hopefully disabling it long enough for him to take Earth. Meanwhile, Marcus is determined to find a way to help Ivanova.
items.title: Endgame

items.summary: Clark is dead and the civil war over, but several issues are unresolved. Ivanova is grief-struck at Marcus death and Lise is missing, and Sheridan must now face the consequences of his actions. He did the right thing - but in the inconvenient way.
items.title: Rising Star

items.summary: Far into the future, someone is archiving video clips pertaining to the fate of Earth and the Interstellar Alliance.
items.title: The Deconstruction of Falling Stars

items.summary: Lochley takes command of Babylon 5 and Byron petitions her for asylum aboard the station. An assassin pledges to kill Sheridan at his inauguration.
items.title: No Compromises

items.summary: Londo collapses from a heart attack, and must battle with his guilt in a dream state. Delenn learns that Lennier is planing to leave Babylon 5 to join the Rangers.
items.title: The Very Long Night of Londo Mollari
items.titleSort: Very Long Night of Londo Mollari

items.summary: A small world plagued by raiders begs the alliance for help. Garibaldi tries forming an intelligence unit of telepaths.
items.title: The Paragon of Animals

items.summary: We see the action from the viewpoint of two maintenance workers as a race of savage aliens attacks the station.
items.title: A View from the Gallery

items.summary: Four rangers come from Minbar with a status report to Delenn, while a Downbelow racketeer decides it's time to get rid of Zack.
items.title: Learning Curve

items.summary: Bester arrives at the station to arrest the Downbelow telepaths, and Londo barely escapes an assassination attempt when the ship he was to be aboard explodes.
items.title: Strange Relations

items.summary: As more telepaths arrive at the station, the denizens of Downbelow start taking notice. Tensions build until one of the telepaths is assaulted, and the others decide to take revenge - against Byron's wishes. Meanwhile, Franklin tries to find out why the Hyach are hiding part of their medical history.
items.title: Secrets of the Soul

items.summary: The Brakiri buy a part of Babylon 5 for a religious ceremony where the dead are supposed to return. Comedians Rebo and Zooty arrive to do a show on the station.
items.title: Day of the Dead

items.summary: Londo starts to suspect that all is not right on Centauri Prime, when a good friend is murdered. On Babylon 5, Byron tries to force the council to give him and his telepaths a homeworld of their own.
items.title: In the Kingdom of the Blind
items.titleSort: In the Kingdom of the Blind

items.summary: The telepaths have barred themselves inside an area of Downbelow, and their telepathic tricks force Lochley to ask Bester for help. G'Kar finds an old friend locked in a cell in the Centauri palace.
items.title: A Tragedy of Telepaths

items.summary: More bloodhound units arrive and the fight with the violent faction of Byron's followers intensifies until the rogues seize Medlab - with Garibaldi and Franklin in it.
items.title: Phoenix Rising

items.summary: It looks like the Alliance will get a break in the investigation of the recent shipping line attacks, when a possible witness may have survived the latest attack and taken refuge on the Drazi homeworld. Garibaldi is sent to find him, but the Intelligence Chief's alcohol problem complicates the mission. G'Kar returns to Babylon 5 to discover that his book has been published, and he is now a revered religious figure.
items.title: The Ragged Edge

items.summary: A telepath murders his roommate and escapes on a ship bound for Babylon 5. Bester is given the job of capturing him, and brings along two PSI Cop interns to show them how he works.
items.title: The Corps Is Mother, the Corps Is Father
items.titleSort: Corps Is Mother, the Corps Is Father

items.summary: Delenn reassigns Lennier to a Ranger training mission on the border of Centauri space, hoping he can find some proof regarding the Centauri involvement in the shipping line attacks. Vir undergoes some dramatic changes when he learns that he is the new Centauri ambassador to Babylon 5.
items.title: Meditations on the Abyss

items.summary: Lennier investigates Centauri signals that may be connected to the attacks. Lyta tries to continue Byron's dream of finding a homeworld for telepaths. Lise visits Garibaldi only to discover he's drinking again.
items.title: Darkness Ascending

items.summary: The evidence collected against the Centauri is presented to the council of the Interstellar Alliance, and a boycott against the Centauri is issued. In reaction, the Centauri withdraw from the Alliance and make it clear that they will circumvent the blockade by force if necessary.
items.title: And All My Dreams, Torn Asunder
items.titleSort: And All My Dreams, Torn Asunder

items.summary: Sheridan finally authorizes the White Star fleet to participate in the war. Delenn travels to Minbar to start a Minbari-Earth joint project to build a prototype White Star destroyer class ship. Vir hires Franklin and Lyta to investigate why the Drazi don't return the bodies from destroyed Centauri ships.
items.title: Movements of Fire and Shadow (1)

items.summary: As Centauri Prime is being bombarded, the Drakh, the real masters behind the war, reveal themselves to Londo. They force him to go along with their plan to alienate the Centauri from the Alliance, and use what's left as their new home.
items.title: The Fall of Centauri Prime (2)

items.summary: Earth Force orders the arrest of Lyta for financing terrorism against the PSI Corps. Sheridan confronts Garibaldi about his drinking. G'Kar struggles with his growing mass of worshippers.
items.title: The Wheel of Fire

items.summary: Tessa Holloran, former Number One of the Mars resistance, arrives with a warning for Lise and Michael: an assassin has been hired to kill them. Meanwhile, G'Kar gets ready to leave, though not everybody is happy about it.
items.title: Objects in Motion

items.summary: It is near the end of 2262, and many changes are abound. Londo, G'Kar and Garibaldi have already left, and Franklin will be taking up his new position on Earth shortly. Finally, Sheridan and Delenn leave for Minbar, where the Alliance's recently finished headquarters are located.
items.title: Objects at Rest

items.summary: Twenty years after his death and resurrection at Z'ha'dum, Sheridan feels his life force ebbing away, and invites some old friends for a final gathering.
items.title: Sleeping in Light

items.summary: Prime Minister Michael Callow faces a shocking dilemma when Princess Susannah, a much-loved member of the Royal Family, is kidnapped.
items.title: The National Anthem

items.summary: In a world where people’s lives consist of riding exercise bikes to gain credits, Bing tries to help a woman get on to a singing competition show.
items.title: Fifteen Million Merits

items.summary: In the near future, everyone has access to a memory implant that records everything humans do, see and hear.
items.title: The Entire History of You

items.summary: After learning about a new service that lets people stay in touch with the deceased, a lonely, grieving Martha reconnects with her late lover.
items.title: Be Right Back

items.summary: Victoria wakes up and cannot remember anything about her life. Everyone she encounters refuses to communicate with her.
items.title: White Bear

items.summary: A failed comedian who voices a popular cartoon bear named Waldo finds himself mixing in politics when TV executives want Waldo to run for office.
items.title: The Waldo Moment

items.summary: A woman desperate to boost her social media score hits the jackpot when she's invited to a swanky wedding. But the trip doesn't go as planned.
items.title: Nosedive

items.summary: An American traveler short on cash signs up to test a revolutionary new gaming system, only to discover the thrills are a little too real.
items.title: Playtest

items.summary: After a virus infects his laptop, a teen faces a daunting choice: carry out orders delivered by text message, or risk having intimate secrets exposed.
items.title: Shut Up and Dance

items.summary: In a seaside town in 1987, a shy young woman and an outgoing party girl strike up a powerful bond that seems to defy the laws of space and time.
items.title: San Junipero

items.summary: After his first battle with an elusive enemy, a soldier begins experiencing unfamiliar sensations and strange technical glitches.
items.title: Men Against Fire

items.summary: The death of a journalist at the center of a social media firestorm leads a veteran detective and her tech-savvy apprentice to a chilling discovery.
items.title: Hated in the Nation

items.summary: Capt. Robert Daly presides over his crew with wisdom and courage, but a new recruit will soon discover nothing on this spaceship is what it seems.
items.title: USS Callister

items.summary: Worried about her daughter's safety, single mom Marie signs up for a cutting-edge device that monitors the girl's whereabouts.
items.title: Arkangel

items.summary: Architect Mia scrambles to keep a dark secret under wraps, while insurance investigator Shazia harvests people's memories of a nearby accident scene.
items.title: Crocodile

items.summary: Paired up by a dating program that puts an expiration date on all relationships, Frank and Amy soon begin to question the system's logic.
items.title: Hang the DJ

items.summary: At an abandoned warehouse, scavengers searching for supplies encounter a ruthless foe and flee for their lives through a bleak wasteland.
items.title: Metalhead

items.summary: On a dusty stretch of highway, a traveler stumbles across a museum that boasts rare artifacts -- and a disturbing main attraction.
items.title: Black Museum

items.summary: When old college friends Danny and Karl reconnect in a VR version of their favorite video game, the late-night sessions yield an unexpected discovery.
items.title: Striking Vipers

items.summary: A London rideshare driver ignites an international crisis when he kidnaps a worker from a social media company.
items.title: Smithereens

items.summary: A lonely teen becomes obsessed with a robot doll based on her pop star idol, Ashley O - just as the real Ashley's life begins to unravel.
items.title: Rachel, Jack and Ashley Too

items.summary: On the emperor's order, Duke Leto Atreides moves from his home planet, Caladan, with his family to lead the planet Arrakis, also known as Dune. After an attack on their stronghold, his son, Paul, and his wife, Lady Jessica, flee into the desert.
items.title: Dune

items.summary: The Lady Jessica and her son, Paul Atreides, manage to contact the native Dune population, known as Fremen.
items.title: Muad'Dib

items.summary: Paul Atreides, who has become known as Paul Muad'Dib, leads a rebellion against the Harkonnen, who have the secret support of the emperor.
items.title: The Prophet

items.summary: Preparations for the Earth/Mars peace conference tighten the tension on Erringwright.

items.summary: Bobbie becomes a political pawn in the struggle between Earth and Mars.

items.summary: Holden leads his crew through the war-torn station on Ganymede.
items.title: Cascade

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Expanse/S02/The EXPANSE - S02 E11 - Here There Be Dragons (720p AMZN WebRip).mp4
items.summary: Bobbie makes a decision that changes her life forever.

items.summary: The Rocinante crew must fight to save the ship.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Expanse/S03/The EXPANSE - S03 E03 - Assured Destruction (720p - AMZN Web-DL).mp4

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Expanse/S03/The EXPANSE - S03 E04 - Reload (720p - AMZN Web-DL).mp4
items.summary: The Rocinante tends to wounded Martian soldiers in exchange for supplies. Avasarala struggles with how to disseminate a key piece of evidence despite being in hiding.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Expanse/S03/The EXPANSE - S03 E05 - Triple Point (720p - AMZN Web-DL).mp4

items.title: Triple Point

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Expanse/S03/The EXPANSE - S03 E06 - Immolation (720p - AMZN Web-DL).mp4
items.summary: The final battle between Earth and Mars threatens the very future of humanity. A new monster is unleashed on Prospero Station. Anna receives the smoking gun she needs.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Expanse/S03/The EXPANSE - S03 E08 - It Reaches Out (720p - AMZN Web-DL).mp4
items.summary: An old friend taunts Holden with the answers he seeks. Naomi struggles to fit in. A mysterious low-level tech aboard the Thomas Prince enacts a terrifying plan.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Expanse/S03/The EXPANSE - S03 E09 - Intransigence (720p - AMZN Web-DL).mp4

items.summary: Drummer and Ashford find themselves trapped with few options for survival; Anna tends to the wounded masses as Melba continues to hunt down her prey; the Rocinante crew struggles to survive as Naomi reunites with her true family.

items.summary: The crew of the Roci investigates a strange protomolecule ruin on an alien planet. Bobbie copes with civilian life on Mars. Drummer and Ashford battle with piracy in the Belt.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Expanse/S04/The EXPANSE - S04 E02 - Jetsam (720p - AMZN Web-DL).mp4
items.summary: Avasarala is blindsided while on a visit to Mars. The Roci crew continue their protomolecule investigation while tensions between the RCE and Belters reach a tipping point. Drummer and Ashford track down a terrorist.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Expanse/S04/The EXPANSE - S04 E03 - Subduction (720p - AMZN Web-DL).mp4.mp4
items.summary: New alien threats emerge on Ilus as Naomi battles health challenges on the planet. Bobbie searches for a missing person on Mars. Avasarala faces a new challenge in the UN.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Expanse/S04/The EXPANSE - S04 E04 - Retrograde (720p - AMZN Web-DL).mp4

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Expanse/S04/The EXPANSE - S04 E05 - Oppressor (720p - AMZN Web-DL).mp4
