items.summary: Irene and Franklin York have a secret: a Chamber buried in their backyard which leads to a strange, deserted planet. But surprising revelations make them reevaluate what they think they know about it.
items.title: To the Stars

items.summary: Franklin and Irene decide what to do with the mysterious man from the Chamber. Single-mother Stella grapples with revealing a family secret to teenaged daughter Toni.
items.title: La Capilla

items.summary: As Irene finds a new zest for life, Franklin becomes more suspicious of Jude. In Argentina, a visitor has something important to give Stella and Toni.
items.title: The Caretaker

items.summary: Irene helps Jude search for someone he has lost. Franklin forms an unexpected bond. Stella begins her mission with help from an old friend.
items.title: Boilermakers

items.summary: Irene goes to new lengths to help Jude. Stella and Denise both visit places that haunt their past. Franklin gives Byron an unexpected gift.
items.title: Driving Lessons

items.summary: A shocking discovery divides Franklin and Irene. Tensions between Stella, Toni, and Nick reach new heights. Jude recruits Denise into his search.
items.title: Dear Franklin

items.summary: Irene, Jude and Denise go on a road trip to find Gabriel, while Franklin and Byron take a journey of their own. Stella and Toni get to know Farnsworth.
items.title: Lake Diving

items.summary: Jude makes a difficult decision, while Franklin and Irene reflect on recent events. Stella’s mission brings her to the Yorks’ doorstep.
items.title: Compensation

items.summary: It's 2417, and the Planetary Union promotes Ed Mercer to Captain of the exploratory vessel The U.S.S. Orville. Ed's enthusiasm for his new position is dampened when his ex-wife, Kelly Grayson, is assigned to be his First Officer. While on their first routine mission, the Orville crew is ambushed by the Krill, a vicious alien race, who are bent on stealing a device that can cause time to accelerate.
items.title: Old Wounds

items.summary: When Ed and Kelly are tricked by a hologram of a ship in distress and find themselves prisoners in a replica of their former home, Alara must step up in her first command of the Orville and attempt a heroic rescue. Meanwhile, Bortus and Klyden receive some happy, yet unexpected news.
items.title: Command Performance

items.summary: The Orville crew is divided between cultures when Bortus and Klyden debate if their newly born offspring should receive a controversial surgery.
items.title: About a Girl

items.summary: Ed and the Orville crew encounter a massive vessel adrift in space, which is in danger of colliding with a star. While some of the crew set out to help the ship's inhabitants, Bortus, Gordon, and John stay behind and fend off a Krill attack on another Union ship
items.title: If the Stars Should Appear

items.summary: After the crew saves a stranded ship and its attractive captain, Ed becomes smitten with the Orville’s new guest, while Kelly suspects all is not what it seems. Meanwhile, Gordon attempts to teach Isaac the art of pulling off a practical joke.
items.title: Pria

items.summary: After the Orville crew defeats a Krill attack on a brand-new colony, the Union sends Ed and Gordon on a dangerous undercover mission to infiltrate a Krill ship and obtain a copy of the Krill bible, the "Anhkana," to better understand the enemy.
items.title: Krill

items.summary: When two Union anthropologists go missing on a planet similar to 21st century Earth, Ed sends a team led by Kelly to find them, but the mission quickly goes awry when they realize the society’s government is completely based on a public voting system to determine punishment.
items.title: Majority Rule

items.summary: Ed and the crew set out to save Dr. Finn, her two sons and Isaac after their shuttle gets thrown into uncharted space and they crash-land on a moon that is light years from the Orville.
items.title: Into the Fold

items.summary: The Orville is called to mediate a peace treaty between two warring cultures, but tensions run even higher between Ed and Kelly when a familiar face boards the ship. Meanwhile Yaphit declares his love for Dr. Finn with surprising results.
items.title: Cupid's Dagger

items.summary: When a fire breaks out on The Orville and a crew member dies, Alara begins to question if she is fit for her job, just as unusual and terrifying things start happening on the ship.
items.title: Firestorm

items.summary: Kelly discovers that Lt. John Lamarr is smarter than he lets on. So, she pushes Ed to consider him for a key leadership position on the ship after The Orville gets damaged by a mysterious spatial anomaly causing harrowing effects to all things living.
items.title: New Dimensions

items.summary: Ed and Kelly consider the possibility of reforging their relationship, but Kelly soon crash-lands on a planet in another universe with Isaac and Gordon.
items.title: Mad Idolatry

items.summary: As The Orville heads towards Moclus for Bortus' special once-a-year ceremony, Ed discovers Kelly has moved on and has started dating. Meanwhile, Gordon asks for John's help in getting game, and Claire turns to Isaac for parenting advice.
items.title: Ja'loja

items.summary: Ed and the crew race to save a small group of survivors on a planet about to be destroyed by its sun. Meanwhile, Bortus and Klyden start marriage counseling when Bortus' obsession with the ship's simulation room gets out of hand.
items.title: Primal Urges

items.summary: Ed, Gordon and Alara visit Alara's home planet of Xelayah.
items.title: Home

items.summary: Ed finds himself behind enemy lines when he crash-lands on a mysterious planet. Meanwhile, Kelly questions why Gordon wants to take the Command Test.
items.title: Nothing Left on Earth Excepting Fishes
items.titleSort: Nothing Left on Earth Excepting Fishes

items.summary: The Orville makes First Contact and a new crew member joins the ship.
items.title: All the World is Birthday Cake
items.titleSort: All the World is Birthday Cake

items.summary: The Orville crew is surprised when Claire's personal life takes an unexpected turn, and Gordon makes an unusual grooming suggestion to Bortus.
items.title: A Happy Refrain

items.summary: One of Bortus's old lovers is assigned to help upgrade the ships defences and makes a surprising admission to Talla.
items.title: Deflectors

items.summary: Ed and the crew travel to Isaac's home planet, Kaylon.
items.title: Identity (1)

items.summary: The Kaylons take control of the Orville with the intention of destroying all biological lifeforms.
items.title: Identity (2)

items.summary: Ed must initiate peace talks with the Krill.
items.title: Blood of Patriots

items.summary: The Orville crew members open a time capsule from 2015.
items.title: Lasting Impressions

items.summary: Ed discovers that Moclans aboard The Orville are harboring a secret.
items.title: Sanctuary

items.summary: A time distortion affects Ed and Kelly's relationship.
items.title: Tomorrow, and Tomorrow, and Tomorrow

items.summary: The crew must contend with the disastrous fallout from Kelly's decision.
items.title: The Road Not Taken

items.summary: The Orville crew deals with the interpersonal aftermath of the battle against the Kaylon.
items.title: Electric Sheep

items.summary: The Orville explores a mysterious region of space.
items.title: Shadow Realms

items.summary: The Orville crew makes a new discovery.
items.title: Mortality Paradox

items.summary: The Orville crew leads a Union delegation to sign a peace treaty with the Krill.
items.title: Gently Falling Rain

items.summary: Tensions between Kelly and the Moclans result when she helps Topa prepare for the Union Point entrance exam.
items.title: A Tale of Two Topas

items.summary: The crew must rescue Gordon from a distant yet familiar world.
items.title: Twice in a Lifetime

items.summary: The Orville discovers a Kaylon with a very special ability.
items.title: From Unknown Graves

items.summary: The crew visit Haveena's sanctuary world and embark on a journey that may leave the Union more vulnerable.
items.title: Midnight Blue

items.summary: The creation of a powerful new weapon puts the Orville crew — and the entire Union — in a political and ethical quandary.
items.title: Domino

items.summary: A celebration is underway aboard the ship.
items.title: Future Unknown

items.summary: Wyoming rancher Royal Abbott discovers an unfathomable mystery at the edge of his property, setting in motion a catastrophic chain of events.
items.title: The Void

items.summary: The Abbott family frantically conspires to cover up their crimes but can’t piece together what has happened to Royal.
items.title: The Land

items.summary: The investigation for the missing Tillerson brother forces Royal to ally with Autumn, until Amy makes an improbable discovery.
items.title: The Time

items.summary: As word spreads about the Tillerson murder, Sheriff Joy interrogates the Abbotts, forcing Royal to wager far more than he can afford to lose.
items.title: The Loss

items.summary: Royal embarks on a quest to investigate the elusive dark mineral that is present on his land, only to intensify his growing rivalry with Autumn.
items.title: The Soil

items.summary: With family ties beginning to fray, Royal takes violent measures to get rid of Autumn, but is foiled when he discovers she has manipulated someone close to him.
items.title: The Family

items.summary: As the Tillersons close in on the Abbott’s secrets, Royal must salvage what is left of his family and livelihood. Autumn orchestrates the unthinkable.
items.title: The Unknown

items.summary: The Abbott family faces a grand reckoning over the course of a single day as the showdown between Royal and Autumn culminates, unearthing a shattering revelation.
items.title: The West

items.summary: In the aftermath of the bison stampede, the Abbott family is more fractured than ever. Royal and Cecilia confront some difficult truths as they fight to keep their family together.
items.title: One Night in Wabang

items.summary: Perry seeks help from an unexpected family member. The Tillersons promise revenge against the Abbotts, while Royal contends with a new threat to the West Pasture.
items.title: Traces to Somewhere

items.summary: Royal and Cecelia become desperate in their attempt to save their ranch. The Tillerson’s are dealt with a startling turn of events.
items.title: Everybody Hurts

items.summary: Lost in time with no way home, Sheriff Joy must navigate a new life among her Shoshone ancestors.
items.title: Ode to Joy

items.summary: Royal rediscovers an unlikely ally; Cecilia grapples with the possibility of Autumn’s identity as Autumn becomes increasingly unhinged.
items.title: All the World's a Stage

items.summary: Autumn’s erratic behavior reaches a fever pitch. Royal and Cecilia take matters into their own hands.
items.title: Do-Si-Do

items.summary: Time is a motherf**ker.
items.title: The End of Innocence

items.summary: An alien hiding in a small Colorado town meets the locals when they ask him to help solve a murder.
items.title: Pilot

items.summary: In his first week at the clinic, Harry struggles to diagnose a strange feeling: human emotion.
items.title: Homesick

items.summary: Harry races to keep his secret safe as Asta is forced to face her own past.
items.title: Secrets

items.summary: Harry travels to the Ute Reservation to help Asta's grandmother, and along the way, learns what it means to belong to a community.
items.title: Birds of a Feather

items.summary: A surprise visitor gives Harry an introduction to marriage, a stressful human institution he needs to familiarize himself with.
items.title: Love Language

items.summary: Harry copes with jealousy when the mayor hires an annoyingly perfect new town doctor.
items.title: Sexy Beast

items.summary: Fearing he's facing failure, Harry enlists an unlikely ally to help find his ship.
items.title: The Green Glow

items.summary: Harry must rely on Asta and D'arcy for survival.
items.title: End of the World as We Know It
items.titleSort: End of the World as We Know It

items.summary: Harry and Asta attend an alien convention.
items.title: Welcome Aliens

items.summary: On the verge of completing his mission, Harry faces his own humanity.
items.title: Heroes of Patience

items.summary: Harry the alien is back on Earth and doesn't remember who he is, and only Asta can keep him safe.
items.title: Old Friends

items.summary: Harry has a plan to save Asta and himself but he must first attend the Sheriff's poker game.
items.title: The Wire

items.summary: Harry meets a woman unlike any other and realizes that she is the key to his new mission.
items.title: Girls' Night

items.summary: Is Harry building another bomb? Asta is going to find out as they go camping on the reservation.
items.title: Radio Harry

items.summary: Harry and Asta's trip is interrupted by an uninvited relative as the town celebrates family.
items.title: Family Day

items.summary: Harry and Asta travel to New York looking for one of his people, but things go horribly wrong.
items.title: An Alien in New York

items.summary: Harry and Asta find what they are looking for but not what they need as danger closes in.
items.title: Escape from New York

items.summary: It's a surprise party as everyone gathers to celebrate Harry, but some dangerous guests cause havoc.
items.title: Alien Dinner Party

items.summary: Asta is overwhelmed with guilt after she, Harry, and D'arcy get rid of the dead body.
items.title: Autopsy

items.summary: Asta helps Harry learn how to deal with his newfound fear of death.
items.title: The Ghost of Bobby Smallwood

items.summary: Asta tells Dan about the shooting while Harry learns what it takes to be a good friend.
items.title: The Weight

items.summary: Halloween comes to Patience, and Harry sheds his human mask. Meanwhile, Ben is trying to promote the new resort to the residents of Patience and meets some resistance.
items.title: The Alien Within

items.summary: After losing the alien baby, Harry learns which alien race is on Earth and it’s not what he expected.
items.title: Harry, a Parent

items.summary: Harry goes head-to-head with one of his biggest enemies.
items.title: Cat and Mouse

items.summary: Harry has an unexpected partner as he tries to infiltrate a military base to find his alien baby. Meanwhile, Asta and Dan help D'arcy to recover and realize, that she's unwilling to leave her new comfort zone.
items.title: Best of Enemies

items.summary: Harry comes face to face with his greatest enemy and makes a choice that may affect Earth forever.
items.title: I Believe in Aliens

items.summary: On the night of her 36th birthday, Nadia meets an untimely end ... then suddenly finds herself back at the party her friends threw for her.
items.title: Nothing in This World Is Easy
items.titleSort: Nothing in This World Is Easy

items.summary: Confused and hung over, Nadia tries to piece together what happened the night before. She tracks down Wardog, the drug dealer with the Israeli joints.
items.title: The Great Escape

items.summary: Nadia's hunt for clues leads her to a Yeshiva school -- but she needs John's help. Out searching for Oatmeal, Nadia befriends a homeless man.
items.title: A Warm Body

items.summary: Meticulous as always, Alan steadies himself for a rendez-vous with his girlfriend. Meanwhile, Nadia's latest discovery sends her reeling.
items.title: Alan's Routine

items.summary: Perturbed by the changes in his routine, Alan shows up at Nadia's birthday party. Nadia tries to make amends to John, and Alan confronts Mike.
items.title: Superiority Complex

items.summary: Nadia and Alan try to figure out how they're connected. Alan can't remember his first death, so Nadia follows him over the course of his night.
items.title: Reflection

items.summary: As the present begins to unravel, Nadia's troubled past comes back to haunt her, and Alan worries they're running out of time.
items.title: The Way Out

items.summary: Nadia and Alan look for each other and finally cross paths at the deli. Something's not right -- but they're not giving up on each other.
items.title: Ariadne

items.summary: Mark is promoted to lead a team who've had their memories surgically divided between their work and personal lives.
items.title: Good News About Hell

items.summary: The team train new hire Helly on macrodata refinement. Mark takes a day off to meet with a mysterious former colleague.
items.title: Half Loop

items.summary: Mark takes the team on a field trip, but Helly continues to rebel. A deteriorating Petey struggles to tell Mark about Lumon’s misdeeds.
items.title: In Perpetuity

items.summary: Irving finds an intriguing book at work. Helly aggressively pursues a meeting with her Outie. Mark attends a funeral with Ms. Selvig.
items.title: The You You Are

items.summary: Irving and Dylan confront Burt about his lies. Mark and Helly discover a strange new department.
items.title: The Grim Barbarity of Optics and Design
items.titleSort: Grim Barbarity of Optics and Design

items.summary: The team angers Cobel by forming an alliance.
items.title: Hide and Seek

items.summary: Mark and the team encounter new security measures from Cobel.
items.title: Defiant Jazz

items.summary: The team prepares a plan. Mark attends Devon and Ricken’s party.
items.title: What's for Dinner?

items.summary: The team discovers troubling revelations.
items.title: The We We Are

items.summary: Mark returns to work under different circumstances. Secrets from the Outie world come to light.
items.title: Hello, Ms. Cobel

items.summary: Mark contemplates the meaning of a message.
items.title: Goodbye, Mrs. Selvig

items.summary: Discoveries are made.

items.summary: Mark and Devon team with an ally. Helly investigates further.
items.title: The After Hours

items.summary: A new crew is assigned to a former Cardassian space station: Deep Space Nine. It is a joint Federation/Bajoran force, with Commander Sisko in charge, but his life is dramatically changed when he is declared the Emissary to the Prophets by a Bajoran priest.
items.title: Emissary (1)

items.summary: Tahna Los, a former Bajoran terrorist during the Occupation, asks Sisko for asylum on DS9. Meanwhile, the station's last Cardassian inhabitant, Garak, possibly a former spy for the Cardassian government, proves an interesting mystery to Dr. Bashir.
items.title: Past Prologue

items.summary: Ibudan, a criminal/murderer Odo has dealt with before, returns to DS9 only to be murdered shortly after. . .leaving Odo to be the prime suspect. Meanwhile, Jake and Nog's trouble making prompt Keiko to do something helpful for the station's children.
items.title: A Man Alone

items.summary: The crew and civilian population of Deep Space Nine begin to gabble when a plague, engineered by the Bajorans as a weapon against the Cardassians, accidentally gets released into the station's atmosphere.
items.title: Babel

items.summary: For the first time an alien comes from the other side of the wormhole. He has ship trouble and seems very reluctant to accept any help. Chief O'Brien quickly finds out he has a secret.
items.title: Captive Pursuit

items.summary: Q, the Enterprise-D's consistent omnipotent annoyance, comes to harass the DS9 crew when his traveling companion, Vash, refuses to travel with Q any longer.
items.title: Q-Less

items.summary: Sins of the Host indeed, as Jadzia Dax is accused of a murder her previous host, Curzon, supposedly committed.
items.title: Dax

items.summary: Rao Vantika, a captured criminal, is badly burned and dies in Bashir's arms. . .but the criminal's captor believes he is still alive.
items.title: The Passenger

items.summary: The Wadi from the Gamma Quadrant are to make first contact and decide to visit DS9. When they catch Quark cheating they let him off by playing a special game.
items.title: Move Along Home

items.summary: The Ferengi's greatest politician and leader, the Grand Nagus, comes to the station. He seems very interested in Quark's bar.
items.title: The Nagus

items.summary: A man named Croden tells Odo he can take him to a place where aliens much like Odo himself exist, which would help Odo find out where he truly comes from.
items.title: Vortex

items.summary: After showing Bajoran spiritual leader Kai Opaka the wormhole, she, Sisko, Bashir and Kira crash land on a moon. Kai Opaka dies and the three meet the unfriendly locals.
items.title: Battle Lines

items.summary: While Sisko tries to negotiate an agreement between two Bajoran factions, he orders O'Brien to escort Bashir to an emergency that endangers a village.
items.title: The Storyteller

items.summary: Kira must convince an old Bajoran farmer to leave a moon becoming uninhabitable due to mining operations. Jake and Nog try to trade off Cardassian yamok sauce.
items.title: Progress

items.summary: Dax investigates if an unusual energy reading is dangerous for the station when all of the sudden people's imaginations really come alive, causing chaos.
items.title: If Wishes Were Horses

items.summary: Lwaxana Troi comes for a political visit and instead hounds Odo for romantic attention. Meanwhile, an alien probe wrecks havoc with the station's computer, leaving Odo and Lwaxana trapped together.
items.title: The Forsaken

items.summary: Out of nowhere the entire station's command staff, apart from Odo, become power hungry and vie to defeat each other by forming secret alliances and plotting assassinations. Needless to say, Odo tries to figure out how this mysterious behavior was influenced.
items.title: Dramatis Personae

items.summary: A Cardassian suffering from Kalla-Nohra, a disease that indicates he served in a labor camp, visits DS9. Kira is determined to convict him as a war criminal.
items.title: Duet

items.summary: Vedek Winn, a candidate in the race for the open Kai position, stirs up trouble on DS9 when she attempts to boycott Keiko's school for not teaching Bajoran religious beliefs.
items.title: In the Hands of the Prophets
items.titleSort: In the Hands of the Prophets

items.summary: Word that a previously thought dead Bajoran resistance legend is still alive sends Kira and Chief O'Brien to Cardassia IV to rescue him; meanwhile "The Circle", a sect of the Bajoran provisional government that is intent on wiping out alien influence, is sneaking into power.
items.title: The Homecoming (1)

items.summary: Kira spends time with Vedek Bareil on Bajor just as "The Circle" begins arming themselves from a mysterious source.
items.title: The Circle (2)

items.summary: As a "Circle"-led Bajoran military tries to occupy the station, a skeleton crew led by Sisko fight to reveal "The Circle's" big secret before they are forced to evacuate themselves. Meanwhile, Kira and Dax lead a mission to reveal the truth about "The Circle" on Bajor.
items.title: The Siege (3)

items.summary: A jealous Trill, who had waited his entire life to receive a symbiont but never had, decides to steal one. . .Dax's!
items.title: Invasive Procedures

items.summary: Political heat rises on the station as Bajorans enter the station with orphaned Cardassians they have adopted.
items.title: Cardassians

items.summary: A new arrival to the station with a special gravity-based disability appeals to Bashir's heart; meanwhile an old associate of Quark's comes to the station to kill the barkeep.
items.title: Melora

items.summary: A female Ferengi, posing as a male to be available to participate in business (a rule STRICTLY forbidden by the Ferengi government), falls for Quark during very important negotiations between the Ferengi and a Gamma Quadrant race.
items.title: Rules of Acquisition

items.summary: Odo relives some terrible and tragic memories of a past investigation when he was the constable on Cardassian-occupied Deep Space Nine, then named Terok Nor.
items.title: Necessary Evil

items.summary: While noted scientist Gideon Seyetik is preparing for an ambitious project, re-igniting a star, Sisko is intrigued by a woman who keeps disappearing.
items.title: Second Sight

items.summary: A race that has been conquered twice over, one of the conquerors being the mysterious Dominion, comes to the station seeking aid and a new home.
items.title: Sanctuary

items.summary: Quark meets his match when a new rival opens a casino opposite Quark's Bar on the Promenade; meanwhile the station is suffering issues of high improbability.
items.title: Rivals

items.summary: Odo and Dr. Mora Pol, Odo's 'father', discover a life form similar to Odo on a Gamma Quadrant planet.
items.title: The Alternate

items.summary: Chief O'Brien, who still doesn't like the good Doctor Bashir, must rely on him when the two are stranded on a planet and O'Brien is infected with a deadly, fast moving disease.
items.title: Armageddon Game

items.summary: Chief O'Brien's world is turned upside down when for no reason whatsoever he is being ignored by his family and friends and is being closed out of every essential job on the station.
items.title: Whispers

items.summary: Sisko and Chief O'Brien discover a colony that lives without technology.
items.title: Paradise

items.summary: Odo and Dax investigate the mysterious disappearance of people from a village. Kira tries to keep a close eye on Quark, while Vedek Bareil unexpectedly visits.
items.title: Shadowplay

items.summary: A Trill named Arjin comes to DS9 to learn what it is to be a Trill with a symbiont but finds his teacher, Dax, to be less than he expected.
items.title: Playing God

items.summary: A Cardassian woman, who was once a former flame of Quark's, visits the station under dubious circumstances.
items.title: Profit and Loss

items.summary: Three legendary Klingons come to DS9 to see if Jadzia Dax will participate in a Blood Oath they made with Jadzia's previous host Curzon.
items.title: Blood Oath

items.summary: The destruction of a Cardassian ship leads Sisko, Dukat, and Sisko's old friend Cal Hudson to the fact that there is an unofficial war between the Maquis and the Cardassians.
items.title: The Maquis (1)

items.summary: Sisko tries to resolve the Maquis crisis by preventing a war, freeing Gul Dukat and offering the defected Hudson the chance to return.
items.title: The Maquis (2)

items.summary: Dr. Bashir fights to save Garak's life when a device implanted in his brain, designed to alleviate pain in the event of torture, begins to malfunction and is slowly killing him.
items.title: The Wire

items.summary: Kira and Bashir find themselves in an alternate universe.
items.title: Crossover

items.summary: Vedek Bareil is targeted by fellow Kai candidate Vedek Winn as having been a collaborator with the Cardassians during the Occupation.
items.title: The Collaborator

items.summary: Chief O'Brien goes through the horrific Cardassian judicial system when he is charged for an unknown crime.
items.title: Tribunal

items.summary: Sisko and Quark and a strange telepathic woman are arrested by Jem'Hadar, soldiers of the Dominion.
items.title: The Jem'Hadar

items.summary: Instead of waiting for the Jem'Hadar to attack, Sisko wants to try a different approach. He wants to take a new class starship to try to find the Founders.
items.title: The Search (1)

items.summary: Odo has found his home and is introduced. Meanwhile Sisko finds out peace talks between the Dominion and the Federation have already started.
items.title: The Search (2)

items.summary: Quark is forced to marry a Klingon widow after he takes credit for the accidental death of her husband, the head of a powerful Klingon House.
items.title: The House of Quark

items.summary: The Trill homeworld is the setting, as Sisko and Bashir take Jadzia home for treatment when she begins experiencing hallucinations after playing a tune she can't recall.
items.title: Equilibrium

items.summary: Kira finds herself on Cardassia as a Cardassian. She is told she is called Iliana Ghemor and was a Cardassian spy.
items.title: Second Skin

items.summary: Odo tries to change the nature of a Jem'Hadar boy that Quark finds, while Sisko tries to break his son's relationship with a 20 year old Dabo girl.
items.title: The Abandoned

items.summary: The station goes into lockdown and the crew is endangered when an old Cardassian security program is accidentally activated.
items.title: Civil Defense

items.summary: Dax falls in love with one of the residents of a multi-dimensional planet, while on DS9 an alien requests a holosuite program of Kira from Quark.
items.title: Meridian

items.summary: Thomas Riker, impersonating Will Riker, steals the Defiant in order to fight with the Maquis. Sisko assist Gul Dukat on Cardassia Prime in stopping the ship entering Cardassian territory.
items.title: Defiant

items.summary: As Lwaxanna Troi visits the station for a Bajoran festival, the crew is stricken with intense romantic attractions to one another.
items.title: Fascination

items.summary: Sisko, Bashir and Dax are accidentally sent to San Francisco in the 21st century due to a transporter malfunction, and must figure out how to get back without changing the time line.
items.title: Past Tense (1)

items.summary: Sisko is forced to take the place of a key historical figure on Earth in 2024 in order to preserve the timeline.
items.title: Past Tense (2)

items.summary: Dr. Bashir must use extraordinary measures to prolong Vedek Bareil's life long enough to allow Bareil to complete sensitive peace negotiations between the Bajorans and the Cardassians.
items.title: Life Support

items.summary: After chasing a fugitive into a cave, Kira gets stuck and is slowly encapsulated by a growing crystal stone while Odo tries to figure out how to free her.
items.title: Heart of Stone

items.summary: Sisko faces a conflict between his Starfleet duties and his role as the Bajoran Emissary when an ancient Bajoran prophecy predicts that a joint Federation-Cardassian project will lead to the destruction of the wormhole.
items.title: Destiny

items.summary: Grand Nagus Zek is acting bizarre by giving away money and rewriting the Rules of Acquisition. Quark attempts to get the old Nagus back.
items.title: Prophet Motive

items.summary: While a Romulan delegation tries to get information about the Dominion, O'Brien gets visions of unpleasant things that are about to happen in the future.
items.title: Visionary

items.summary: After being attacked in the infirmary, Dr. Bashir has a dual mystery on his hands: what has happened to the station while he was out and why is he aging so rapidly now?
items.title: Distant Voices

items.summary: Sisko is kidnapped to impersonate his deceased, mirror universe self to gain Jennifer Sisko's loyalty in the Rebel Alliance.
items.title: Through the Looking Glass

items.summary: After an attempt is made on Garak's life, Odo conducts the investigation on who tried to murder the Cardassian tailor - and why.
items.title: Improbable Cause (1)

items.summary: Now rejoined with his former mentor, Garak is ordered to interrogate Odo about the secrets of his people, while the joined Romulan/Cardassian attack fleet moves towards the Founders' home world on a mission of destruction.
items.title: The Die Is Cast (2)

items.summary: Sisko rebuilds an ancient Bajoran space vessel from the blueprints, and he and Jake take the ship on a trip, attempting to prove that the ancient Bajorans went beyond their solar system without warp drive.
items.title: Explorers

items.summary: Quark and Rom return to the Ferengi home world because their mother has broken the law - by wearing clothes and earning profits, forbidden for women in Ferengi society.
items.title: Family Business

items.summary: News arrives that Kai Winn has also become Bajor's political leader. She asks Kira to negotiate with an old resistance friend about returning soil reclamators.
items.title: Shakaar

items.summary: Dax asks the crew to join her Zhian'tara ritual. The memories of her former hosts will take over their bodies. Nog is preparing for Starfleet Academy.
items.title: Facets

items.summary: The Defiant is off to show the Federation's presence to the new Tzenkethi government. While underway the ship malfunctions and Bashir is suspected of sabotage.
items.title: The Adversary

items.summary: Sisko becomes uncomfortable when the Klingons station a task force to help defend against the Dominion. Worf is summoned to find out their true intentions.
items.title: The Way of the Warrior (1)

items.summary: Melanie, an aspiring writer, wants to know why Jake Sisko stopped writing at 40. Jake tells how his father died in an accident and then suddenly reappeared.
items.title: The Visitor

items.summary: Bashir is asked to help a group of renegade Jem'Hadar break their addiction to ketracel white. Meanwhile Worf is dissatisfied with the way Odo runs security.
items.title: Hippocratic Oath

items.summary: Kira and Gul Dukat go after the lost prison ship Ravinok. Dukat has a secret. Meanwhile Kasidy Yates tries to find work near Bajor, leaving Sisko uncomfortable.
items.title: Indiscretion

items.summary: Lenara Kahn, the new host of the wife of Dax's former host Torias, comes to the station. While they're not allowed to renew their relation, there's still a spark.
items.title: Rejoined

items.summary: A damaged Defiant must play a dangerous game of cat-and-mouse with two Jem'hadar ships inside a gas giant.
items.title: Starship Down

items.summary: Quark and Rom take Nog to Earth and Starfleet Academy, but a malfunction with the ship takes the crew back in time, to Roswell New Mexico in 1947.
items.title: Little Green Men

items.summary: Worf, Dax and the Klingon Dahar master Kor set out to find an ancient lost relic: the Sword of Kahless.
items.title: The Sword of Kahless

items.summary: When an transporter emergency turns the command crew into holosuite characters, Bashir's James Bond fantasy takes on a deadly reality.
items.title: Our Man Bashir

items.summary: Sisko travels to Earth when a bombing at a Federation conference is determined to be the work of Changelings.
items.title: Homefront (1)

items.summary: When Starfleet institutes martial law to combat the Changeling Menace, Sisko begins to question if the Dominion is the real threat.
items.title: Paradise Lost (2)

items.summary: First Minister Shakaar visits the station, despite a threat of assassination. He falls in love with Kira much to Odo's dismay.
items.title: Crossfire

items.summary: Dukat returns, stripped of his prestige, to escort Kira to a Cardassian conference about the Dominion. But an attack by a Klingon raider may give Dukat a chance to redeem himself in the eyes of his government.
items.title: Return to Grace

items.summary: Worf's brother Kurn asks him to perform a death rite to regain his lost honor. Meanwhile Kira and O'Brien investigate Klingon activity near the Bajoran border.
items.title: Sons of Mogh

items.summary: Unfair working conditions and pay cuts cause Rom to organize a union of the employees of Quark's Bar. Meanwhile Worf still finds it hard to settle on the station.
items.title: Bar Association

items.summary: A man claiming to be the emissary comes through the wormhole. Sisko is happy to give up his position. Meanwhile Keiko returns and O'Brien stops spending time with Bashir.
items.title: Accession

items.summary: When Worf destroys a civilian shuttle during an engagement with the Klingons, an extradition hearing is held to see if he must face charges.
items.title: Rules of Engagement

items.summary: O'Brien tries to re-integrate to life on the station after serving 20 years in a virtual prison.
items.title: Hard Time

items.summary: When the Mirror Universe counterpart of Sisko's deceased wife lures Jake to the other side, Sisko must follow and help the human resistance against the Alliance's forces.
items.title: Shattered Mirror

items.summary: A mysterious woman approaches Jake about his future as a writer. Odo promises to do whatever it takes to help Lwaxana Troi keep her baby over the father's wishes - even if it means marrying her himself.
items.title: The Muse

items.summary: Sisko must face betrayal when evidence surfaces that Kasidy is smuggling for the Maquis. Meanwhile Garak makes acquaintance with Ziyal.
items.title: For the Cause

items.summary: A renegade group of Jem'Hadar plunders Deep Space Nine. Sisko agrees to a combat operation with loyal Jem'Hadar to prevent the renegades completing a planetary gateway.
items.title: To the Death

items.summary: Bashir tries to help a planet in the grips of a Dominion-engineered plague that guarantees a painful death.
items.title: The Quickening

items.summary: Quarks hears on Ferenginar he is going to die. Rom convinces him to sell his remains. After an accident, Bashir has to move Keiko's baby to Kira's womb.
items.title: Body Parts

items.summary: Odo is suddenly struck by illness. He is barely able to hold shape. Bashir and Odo see no other alternative then going to the Founders. Garak wants to come along.
items.title: Broken Link

items.summary: With the war between Klingons and Federation intensifying, Sisko must make a plan to expose Gowron as a changeling. Odo is still having trouble with becoming a solid.
items.title: Apocalypse Rising

items.summary: The crew is forced to retreat in a crashed Jem'Hadar ship after an attack by the Jem'Hadar. They get the feeling there's something very important about this ship.
items.title: The Ship

items.summary: While Worf helps Quark to pursue his former wife Grilka, O'Brien and Kira grow uncomfortably close to each other.
items.title: Looking for par'Mach in All the Wrong Places
items.titleSort: Looking for par'Mach in All the Wrong Places

items.summary: Jake, reporting from the front lines, sees what war truly is.
items.title: Nor the Battle to the Strong
items.titleSort: Nor the Battle to the Strong

items.summary: An alien entity has possessed Keiko's body and is holding it hostage until O'Brien completes an assignment for it.
items.title: The Assignment

items.summary: Darvin, a disgraced Klingon spy, travels back in time to alter some events to his likings. The DS9 crew must find what he's trying to change and prevent it without altering the time line. They'll have to blend in with the crew from Star Trek: The Original Series.
items.title: Trials and Tribble-ations

items.summary: While vacationing on Risa, Worf and Dax meet a group of fundamentalist protesters who claim that the Federation has gone soft.
items.title: Let He Who Is Without Sin...
items.titleSort: Let He Who Is Without Sin...

items.summary: Sisko, Dax, Odo and Garak find themselves in the past when the Cardassians controlled the station, and a crime that Odo investigated may be the key.
items.title: Things Past

items.summary: When Odo and Quark crash land, they must put aside their differences to climb a mountain to signal for help. Jake and Nog try to be roommates, but their different styles clash.
items.title: The Ascent

items.summary: Sisko begins having visions that may show him how to best help Bajor, but they're killing him.
items.title: Rapture

items.summary: A mysterious assassin begins wiping out all the members of Kira's old resistance cell.
items.title: The Darkness and the Light

items.summary: The discovery of an infant Changeling gives Odo a chance to correct what he sees as the "mistakes" in his upbringing. But as Starfleet's pressure for results grows, he has to turn to his "father," Dr. Mora
items.title: The Begotten

items.summary: When the traitorous Eddington returns, Sisko will go to any lengths to capture him.
items.title: For the Uniform

items.summary: A coded message from the Gamma Quadrant leads Garak to believe his mentor, Enabran Tain, is still alive. He and Worf seek him out, only to discover something much worse: a Dominion invasion fleet poised to attack the Alpha Quadrant.
items.title: In Purgatory's Shadow (1)

items.summary: The station readies for a Dominion attack. Worf and Garak meet some unexpected friends in a Dominion Prison camp.
items.title: By Inferno's Light (2)

items.summary: Dr. Bashir is selected to be the model for the next-generation of Emergency Medical Hologram (EMH). But he balks when his parents are invited to the station to be interviewed by the EMH programmer, Dr. Zimmerman. There is a dark secret in his family that he's afraid that his parents will reveal.
items.title: Doctor Bashir, I Presume?

items.summary: Odo becomes romantically attached to a woman working with the Orion Syndicate.
items.title: A Simple Investigation

items.summary: Quark must wrestle with his conscience when he becomes involved with arms merchants.
items.title: Business as Usual

items.summary: When a Cardassian official that thinks of Kira as his daughter is dying, he agrees to reveal all he knows to her. But the experience dredges up Kira's memories of her own father's death.
items.title: Ties of Blood and Water

items.summary: Quark doesn't know whether to be panicked or overjoyed when he learns that his mother is the new lover of the Grand Nagus.
items.title: Ferengi Love Songs

items.summary: Dax and Worf accompany Martok on his first command since being held by the Dominion. But the ship they are given hasn't seen victory in months and the crew is near mutinous.
items.title: Soldiers of the Empire

items.summary: The DS9 crew discovers a small colony on a remote world that was originally populated by them 200 years earlier due to a time travel accident with the Defiant. The current colonists' lives depend on making sure that the accident happens again, even though they've now forewarned the crew that it will happen. Each crew member needs to decide if they are willing to give up their lives on DS9 in order to preserve the history of the colony.
items.title: Children of Time

items.summary: Driven to desperation by the Dominion, the Maquis launch a massive bio-weapons strike towards Cardassia. Sisko must trust the traitor Eddington to try to stop them.
items.title: Blaze of Glory

items.summary: While salvaging components from DS9's sister station, the crew run afoul of a "surprise" left behind by the Cardassians.
items.title: Empok Nor

items.summary: Jake and Nog go through hell and high water, from participating in an auction to dealing with the Dominion, to receiving a Willie Mays baseball card to cheer up the war-fatigued Captain Sisko.
items.title: In the Cards

items.summary: With the continuing battalions of Jem'Hadar entering the Alpha Quadrant in preparation for war, Sisko decides to mine the wormhole to prevent further troop movement. This provokes a confrontation between the Dominion and the Federation, forcing Sisko to abandon DS9.
items.title: Call to Arms

items.summary: Borrowing a captured Jem'Hadar attack ship, Sisko and crew embark on a mission to destroy the hidden base where all of the ketracel-white is stored for the entire Alpha Quadrant.
items.title: A Time to Stand

items.summary: Sisko and his crew crash on a barren world when their commandeered Jem'Hadar ship is shot down. They encounter Jem'Hadar who crashed there earlier, and have taken Nog and Garak hostage in exchange for medical aid for their Vorta overseer.
items.title: Rocks and Shoals

items.summary: Serving with his recruit son aboard a Klingon vessel, Worf finds his relationship with his son strained. Meanwhile, strained relationships abound on DS9 between Major Kira and Gul Dukat.
items.title: Sons and Daughters

items.summary: After forming an attack plan on the Dominion, Sisko relinquishes command of the Defiant to Dax after accepting a promotion. On DS9, the resistance faces discovery when Odo links with another changeling.
items.title: Behind the Lines

items.summary: Sisko mounts an attack to re-take DS9, while Rom faces charges as an enemy of the Dominion state.
items.title: Favor the Bold (1)

items.summary: The Federation attacks DS9 in hopes of keeping the mine field in the wormhole intact, while the Dominion waits entrance to the Alpha Quadrant from the other side.
items.title: Sacrifice of Angels (2)

items.summary: Suddenly desiring to wed within the week on DS9, Worf and Jadzia go through their own Klingon rituals: Worf on a four day bachelor party with the male members of the crew & Jadzia deals with her prospective mother-in-law, who totally opposes the idea of "an alien" marrying into her Klingon household.
items.title: You Are Cordially Invited

items.summary: Major Kira takes a romantic interest in a Bajoran radical from the other universe who transports himself into her universe and onto DS9.
items.title: Resurrection

items.summary: A group of genetically engineered humans are brought to Dr. Bashir on DS9 in hopes of integrating them with the rest of the universe.
items.title: Statistical Probabilities

items.summary: At the request of the Grand Nagus, Quark puts together a mission to rescue Quark's mother, who is in the hands of the Dominion.
items.title: The Magnificent Ferengi

items.summary: After being attacked by Cardassian forces, Sisko gets stranded with a very psychotic Gul Dukat, who was being transported to his trial. Meanwhile the crew of the Defiant races to rescue survivors.
items.title: Waltz

items.summary: A former patron of Quark's bequeaths everything to him.
items.title: Who Mourns for Morn?

items.summary: Captain Sisko has a full sensory vision of himself as an under-appreciated science fiction magazine writer in 1950s America.
items.title: Far Beyond the Stars

items.summary: An attack by the Dominion on Sisko's ship endangers Dax and her crew aboard as she leads them into an anomaly that shrinks them to a very minute size. Unfortunately, they were being held stable by Sisko within a tractor beam, which was discontinued during the attack.
items.title: One Little Ship

items.summary: Chief O'Brien goes undercover to infiltrate an Orion crime ring.
items.title: Honor Among Thieves

items.summary: Worf and Jadzia travel to the badlands to procure some information on the Dominion from a traitorous Cardassian. Bashir wants to engage in a holo-suite spy simulation, but O'Brien prefers to brush up on his tongo game after watching Jadzia lose to Quark.
items.title: Change of Heart

items.summary: After receiving some disturbing information from Gul Dukat, Major Kira seeks Sisko's approval as Emissary to travel back in time to find out the truth about her mother. Meanwhile, Chief O'Brien and Dr. Bashir discuss a holosuite program surrounding the Battle of the Alamo.
items.title: Wrongs Darker Than Death or Night
items.titleSort: Wrongs Darker Than Death or Night

items.summary: Dr. Bashir's plans to attend a medical conference at a breezy resort are canceled when Starfleet Intelligence boards DS9, suspecting the doctor of treason.
items.title: Inquisition

items.summary: To save the Federation in a critical scheme, Sisko comes to realize that he must violate its fundamental principles to do so.
items.title: In the Pale Moonlight

items.summary: Odo is schooled in the ways of romance by a holographic programmed lounge singer.
items.title: His Way

items.summary: Sisko runs afoul of Kai Winn when he removes a Bajoran artifact from an archaeological dig after he receives a vision from the Prophets.
items.title: The Reckoning

items.summary: Jake and Nog's runabout comes under attack from the Jem'Hadar. They are rescued by the Valiant, a ship manned by Red Squad, a elite group of young Starfleet cadets.
items.title: Valiant

items.summary: Quark's mother and the Grand Nagus show up on DS9, announcing a new amendment to the Bill of Opportunities he has instituted on the home planet of Ferenganar, and then follows up with the announcement, that, due to the new amendment, chaos has followed and he has been deposed.
items.title: Profit and Lace

items.summary: The Chief's daughter gets caught in a time displacement and when they get her back, she is considerably older.
items.title: Time's Orphan

items.summary: As the Defiant races to a shipwrecked officer who is days away, the crew keeps in contact with her. Meanwhile, Jake follows Quark's latest scheme for story research.
items.title: The Sound of Her Voice

items.summary: When Sisko is picked to head up an attack on the Cardassian homeworld, the Prophets appear to him in a vision, warning him of impending doom if he leaves the station.
items.title: Tears of the Prophets

items.summary: Having returned to Earth a couple of months ago, Sisko waits for the Prophets to instruct him on what to do next. When he receives one, he begins searching for the woman behind the face in the sand in his vision. Meanwhile, back on DS9, Kira deals with a promotion and handling the decisions surrounding her command, and finding herself wishing for the return of Sisko. And Worf deals with the loss of his wife, Jadzia Dax.
items.title: Image in the Sand

items.summary: Ezri joins Sisko and his family on his quest for the Orb of the Emissary. Colonel Kira mounts a blockade around a Bajoran moon where the Romulan alliance has deposited an ammunitions dump, claiming it in the name of defense for a Romulan hospital. And Quark joins the rest of the DS9 crew as they join Worf aboard a Klingon warship as they mount a dangerous mission in Jadzia Dax's name in an effort to get her spirit into Stovokohr, the Klingon equivalent of Heaven.
items.title: Shadows and Symbols

items.summary: Sisko tries to convince Ezri to stay in Starfleet and serve aboard DS9, as Ezri tries to get to know Jadzia's friends aboard the station, especially Worf. Meanwhile, Garak tries to deal with a severe bout of claustrophobia.
items.title: Afterimage

items.summary: A Vulcan captain challenges Sisko to a game of baseball.
items.title: Take Me Out to the Holosuite
items.titleSort: Take Me Out to the Holosuite

items.summary: Dr. Bashir attempts to bring one of his genetically engineered friends out of the catatonic state she is in, and when he is successful, he begins to fall for her.
items.title: Chrysalis

items.summary: A Vorta offers Odo valuable information on the Dominion in exchange for asylum. Meanwhile, Nog tries his Ferengi knowledge as he wheels and deals for a valuable piece of equipment for Chief O'Brien.
items.title: Treachery, Faith, and the Great River
items.titleSort: Treachery, Faith, and the Great River

items.summary: An aged Kor requests an opportunity to die with honor as a warrior.
items.title: Once More Unto the Breach

items.summary: Capt. Sisko and his away team volunteer to stay with a besieged unit at an isolate outpost.
items.title: The Siege of AR-558

items.summary: Kira is kidnapped and taken to Empok Nor by a member of a Pah'Wraith cult and discovers the group leader is Gul Dukat.
items.title: Covenant

items.summary: Severely depressed at his serious war wound, Nog retreats into Vic Fontaine's holosuite program while the singer tries to help him.
items.title: It's Only a Paper Moon

items.summary: Ezri travels to her family home in search of Chief O'Brien who has discovered a murdered woman connected with the family and the Orion Syndicate.
items.title: Prodigal Daughter

items.summary: Quark and Rom have to rescue Grand Nagus Zek who is being held captive in the Alternate Universe.
items.title: The Emperor's New Cloak

items.summary: To help find the apparently untraceable murderer of a young ensign, who had recently received a battlefield decoration, Ezri Dax reluctantly calls up the residual consciousness remnant of her symbiont’s past, the psychopathic murderer host, Joran.
items.title: Field of Fire

items.summary: After searching out and finding Odo, another changeling asks him to leave DS9 with him, even though the rest of the crew aren't convinced the new changeling is not part of the Founders.
items.title: Chimera

items.summary: When a programming glitch won't go away, mobsters take over Vic's and open for business, but the DS9 gang takes it personal when their favorite hangout is no longer their favorite, and they plan to get the new management ousted.
items.title: Badda-Bing, Badda-Bang

items.summary: While making plans to attend a medical conference on the Romulan home world, Dr. Bashir is contacted by Sloane of Section 31 and recruited to determine the health of a high-ranking Romulan official. Things turn more desperate though, when the ranking Starfleet admiral traveling with him, who knows about Section 31's interest in the conference mysteriously suffers a brain aneurysm. Dr. Bashir's curiosity is peaked when he finds out Sloane is traveling with the group as well.
items.title: Inter Arma Enim Silent Leges

items.summary: When the ship Worf was serving on is attacked in battle and all search efforts are abandoned, Ezri takes a runabout in search of him against Sisko's orders. Meanwhile, Sisko proposes to Cassidy Yates.
items.title: Penumbra

items.summary: The Prophets have told Sisko that they do not agree with his impending marriage. Ezri and Worf are captured by Dominion forces. Some of the Cardassians are beginning to regret their alliance with the Dominion, as Gul Dukat, disguised as a Bajoran, sets foot on DS9.
items.title: 'Til Death Do Us Part

items.summary:
Kai Winn gets unknowingly involved with Gul Dukat, disguised as a Bajoran. Tensions are further escalated between Weyoun and Gul Damar as the Dominion gather to sign a peace treaty with the Breen, including certain concessions of unknown territories by the Cardassians.

Ezri and Worf try to escape the Cardassian home world.
items.title: Strange Bedfellows

items.summary: After the Breen attack Earth there are mixed emotions abound on DS9. Having revealed her secret regarding the Prophets to the disguised Dukat, Kai Winn turns her back on them, only to be convinced by Dukat to embrace the Pah Wraiths. On the home world of Cardassia, Legate Damar mounts a resistance to the Dominion.
items.title: The Changing Face of Evil

items.summary: Kira gets sent behind Cardassian lines in an effort to train them in resistance fighting. When Dr. Bashir learns of the deadly disease that Odo is infected with, he's met with barriers when trying to obtain his medical records from Starfleet. Martok gets blindsided by Gowron when he arrives on DS9, announcing that he has assumed command of the Klingon fleet.
items.title: When It Rains...

items.summary: Odo is affected by the disease threatening to eliminate his race more than he lets on. Kira has to deal with the Cardassian's dislike of her. Even though General Martok sees Chancellor Gowron's move as part of a political vendetta, he does nothing about it.
items.title: Tacking Into the Wind

items.summary: Dr. Bashir and Chief O'Brien go to extreme measures to try and track down a cure for Odo.
items.title: Extreme Measures

items.summary: Odo begins his recovery from the deadly disease as Dr. Bashir informs him of Section 31's intentions of wiping out his race. A resistance mission goes bad for Kira and Garak and they end up hiding in the basement of the house that Garak grew up in, where they learned that Legate Damar has apparently become a casualty of war, despite him also hiding with them. Quark is chosen by the Grand Nagas as his successor upon his impending retirement to Risa.
items.title: The Dogs of War

items.summary: Sisko leads, what he hopes will be, a final all-out assault on Cardassia Prime. Kira and Garak mount a suicidal assault on the Cardassian headquarters occupied by the Dominion, who in turn kill innocent women and children village by village in retaliation for the Resistance's attacks.
items.title: What You Leave Behind (1)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.1/Star.Trek.TNG.S01E01-E02 - Encounter at Farpoint.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 41153.7. The new commander of the recently built U.S.S. Enterprise (NCC1701-D), Captain Jean- Luc Picard  takes the crew on their first mission to discover the secret of Farpoint Station. During their journey, they encounter an omnipotent being known as Q. Q accuses humanity of barbarism, and places humanity on trial. Jean-Luc must prove otherwise or the human race will be annihilated.

items.titleSort: Where No One Has Gone Before

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.1/Star.Trek.TNG.S01E06 - Where No One Has Gone Before.mkv

items.summary: Stardate: 41255.6. Picard is forced to choose between friendship and the Prime Directive when Wesley Crusher is sentenced to death for accidentally breaking the law on Rubicon III.

items.summary: Stardate: 41723.9. The Ferengi hand over an old ship which Picard once captained, the U.S.S. Stargazer. The Ferengi have installed a mind altering device that alters Picard's mind to make him think that he is reliving a past battle, and the target is the Enterprise.
items.title: The Battle

items.summary: Stardate: 41590.5. Q places the senior crew of the Enterprise in a war game that pits them against a boar-faced, Napoleonic enemy.
items.title: Hide and Q

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.1/Star.Trek.TNG.S01E10 - Hide and Q.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 41294.6. The mother of Deanna Troi, Lwaxana,  pays a surprise visit to the Enterprise and announces the prearranged marriage of Deanna to the son of her mother's late husband's best friend.
items.title: Haven

items.summary: Stardate: 41997.7. Picard, Dr. Crusher and Data are placed in great danger when the holodeck malfunctions while they are running a Dixon Hill program, which pits them against 1940's mobsters.
items.title: The Big Goodbye

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.1/Star.Trek.TNG.S01E12 - The Big Goodbye.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 41242.4.  While exploring his homeworld, the crew of the Enterprise find android parts that are identical to Data's. When assembled, an 'evil' twin of Data named Lore is revived.
items.title: Datalore

items.summary: Stardate: 41636.9. The Enterprise discovers the male crew of a crashed Federation freighter are hiding as fugitives on the planet Angel One, which is dominated and ruled by women.
items.title: Angel One

items.summary: Stardate: 41365.9. While undergoing repairs, the Bynar Engineers steal the Enterprise to save their planet from destruction.
Stardate: 41309.5. The aging and terminally ill Starfleet Admiral Mark Jameson, who is negotiating the release of hostages, suddenly begins growing younger through an unexplained phenomenon.
items.title: Too Short a Season

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.1/Star.Trek.TNG.S01E16 - Too Short a Season.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 41509.1. The children of the Enterprise, including Wesley Crusher, are abducted by a race of sterile people who are unable to have children of their own.
items.title: When the Bough Breaks

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.1/Star.Trek.TNG.S01E17 - When the Bough Breaks.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 41463.9. The members of an away team investigating the death of an engineer encounter vengeful microscopic life forms.
items.title: Home Soil

items.summary: Stardate: 41416.2. While Wesley takes the entrance exam to Starfleet Academy, the Enterprise is investigated by the Inspector General's office and Picard's competency is questioned.
items.title: Coming of Age

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.1/Star.Trek.TNG.S01E19 - Coming of Age.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 41503.7. Two Klingons, rescued by the Enterprise, try to take over the ship.
items.title: Heart of Glory

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.1/Star.Trek.TNG.S01E20 - Heart of Glory.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 41798.2. The crew encounters bizarre phenomena while searching for the missing U.S.S. Drake.
items.title: The Arsenal of Freedom

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.1/Star.Trek.TNG.S01E21 - The Arsenal of Freedom.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: Unknown. Picard attempts to break an ancient co-dependency between two species on one planet without violating the Prime Directive.
items.title: Symbiosis

items.summary: Stardate: 41601.3. When Troi's shuttle crashes on an alien planet, a new being is discovered: an entity that thrives on the suffering of others.
items.title: Skin of Evil

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.1/Star.Trek.TNG.S01E23 - Skin of Evil.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 41697.9. Picard meets an old flame, whose husband has created a haywire dimensional experiment.
items.title: We'll Always Have Paris

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.1/Star.Trek.TNG.S01E24 - We'll Always Have Paris.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 41775.5. The strange behavior of high-ranking officers leads Picard to uncover a twisted alien conspiracy within Starfleet.
items.title: Conspiracy

items.summary: Stardate: 41986.0. A derelict satellite is found with cryonically frozen humans aboard as the USS Enterprise is sent to investigate the destruction of outposts near Romulan space.
items.title: The Neutral Zone

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.1/Star.Trek.TNG.S01E26 - The Neutral Zone.mkv
items.title: Episode 26

items.summary: Stardate: 42073.1. Troi undergoes a mysterious pregnancy when the Enterprise tries to escape from a system that has recently fallen victim to a deadly plague.
items.title: The Child

items.summary: Stardate: 42193.6. A mysterious life form known as the 'Nagilum' threatens the life of the crew in his attempt to understand humanity.
items.title: Where Silence Has Lease

items.summary: Stardate: 42286.3. Data and Geordi become involved with a holodeck program about Sherlock Holmes and his investigations, when they create Sherlock's arch nemesis, Moriarty; however, modifications to the Moriarty character include the capability of out-smarting Data, which leads to some unexpected consequences.
items.title: Elementary, Dear Data

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.2/Star.Trek.TNG.S02E04 - The Outrageous Okona.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 42402.7. The Enterprise is placed in a compromising situation when the captain of a disabled starship places the crew in the middle of a love triangle.
items.title: The Outrageous Okona

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.2/Star.Trek.TNG.S02E05 - Loud As A Whisper.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 42477.2. A deaf-mute mediator meets with disaster while being escorted by the Enterprise.
items.title: Loud as a Whisper

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.2/Star.Trek.TNG.S02E06 - The Schizoid Man.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 42437.5. Data is possessed by the consciousness of a brilliant scientist. However, it has a disturbing impact on Data's personality.
items.title: The Schizoid Man

items.summary: Stardate: 42494.8. A mysterious hyper-ageing sickness kills the crew of a Federation cargo ship, and Dr. Pulaski must race against time to find a cure.
items.title: Unnatural Selection

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.2/Star.Trek.TNG.S02E08 - A Matter Of Honor.mkv
items.summary: Commander Riker participates in an officer's exchange program which lands him an assignment on a Klingon Bird-of-Prey.  Meanwhile, a Bezite ensign has trouble assimilating to the routines of the Enterprise.
items.title: A Matter of Honor

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.2/Star.Trek.TNG.S02E09 - The Measure Of A Man.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 42523.7. When Data's rights as a sentient individual are placed under trial, Starfleet forces Riker into a position where he must prove that Data is only an Android.
items.title: The Measure of a Man

items.summary: Stardate: 42568.8. Wesley falls in love with a passenger the Enterprise is escorting, who has the secret ability to shape-shift.
items.title: The Dauphin

items.summary: Stardate: 42609.1. A strange power source disables the Enterprise's computer systems, damages Data's programming and leaves the ship and crew vulnerable to a Romulan attack.
items.title: Contagion

items.summary: Stardate: 42625.4. An away team is trapped in an alien environment based around a novel entitled 'The Hotel Royale.'
items.title: The Royale

items.summary: Stardate: 42679.2. Picard encounters his double from six hours in the future, whose Enterprise had been destroyed.
items.title: Time Squared

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.2/Star.Trek.TNG.S02E14 - The Icarus Factor.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 42686.4. Riker is promoted to Captain of another Federation ship. Worf must confront his past and his Klingon heritage.
items.title: The Icarus Factor

items.summary: Stardate: 42695.3. Wesley must investigate the causes of strange tectonic activity on the planet where Data's pen pal lives.
items.title: Pen Pals

items.summary: Stardate: 42761.3. Q hurls the Enterprise into the Delta Quadrant and introduces the Federation to a powerful new enemy that may destroy the Alpha Quadrant: The Borg.
items.title: Q Who

items.summary: Stardate: 42779.1. A race known as the Pakleds kidnap Geordi La Forge. Picard must face surgery when he is left in a near-dead state.
items.title: Samaritan Snare

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.2/Star.Trek.TNG.S02E18 - Up The Long Ladder.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 42823.2. Picard must convince two dying civilizations that they must co-exist on the same planet to survive, however, they have other plans to ensure their survival: in the form of clones of the Enterprise crew.
items.title: Up the Long Ladder

items.summary: Stardate: 42859.2. While being escorted to a Federation conference by the Enterprise, Lwaxana hunts for a man to satisfy her needs when her sex-drive is quadrupled during a natural mid-life cycle.
items.title: Manhunt

items.summary: Stardate: 42901.3. Worf is re-united with his former lover, K'Ehleyr, while the Enterprise is ordered to intercept a Klingon ship whose crew has been in stasis for a century.
items.title: The Emissary

items.summary: Stardate: 42923.4. Trouble begins when a Ferengi warship stumbles over a war simulation between Riker and Picard, each on different ships, and begins attacking them.
items.title: Peak Performance

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.2/Star.Trek.TNG.S02E22 - Shades of Gray.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 42976.1. Riker is infected with an alien organism that takes over his mind. Dr. Pulaski must force Riker's mind back to a state where it can access primitive survival skills.
items.title: Shades of Gray

Riker and Soren, a member of the J'naii race, begin preparing to rescue the craft, and the two strike up a friendship. Their relationship develops quickly as the pair question each other about mating habits, since the J'naii are androgynous and do not identify themselves as either male or female. Despite this difference, sparks begin to fly between them.

items.title: Timescape

items.summary: Stardate: 46982.1. The Borg return to threaten the Federation under the new leadership of Lore. Data experiences a disturbing facet of human emotions - he feels pleasure after killing a Borg drone.
items.title: Descent (1)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.7/Star.Trek.TNG.S07E01 - Descent Part II.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 47025.4. Data abducts Picard, Troi and Geordi and holds them prisoners of the Borg, while he derives pleasure from being evil. Dr. Crusher is left in command of the Enterprise as it comes under attack from a Borg vessel.
items.title: Descent (2)

items.summary: Stardate: Unknown. During an exchange program, Picard's shuttle crashes on an unknown planet where he is rescued by the sole survivor of another crash.
items.title: Liaisons

items.summary: Stardate: 47215.5. Geordi defies direct orders from Captain Picard in an attempt to rescue his mother who had recently been reported as missing.
items.title: Interface

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.7/Star.Trek.TNG.S07E04 - Gambit Part I.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 47135.2. An away team investigates the apparent death of Jean-Luc Picard who was supposedly killed in a bar fight. When Riker is abducted by a band of criminals who loot archaeological digs, he is shocked to find Picard alive and well, and undercover as a renegade archaeologist.
items.title: Gambit (1)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.7/Star.Trek.TNG.S07E05 - Gambit Part II.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 47160.1. Picard and Riker covertly work together in an attempt to find out why the criminals are looting archaeological digs.
items.title: Gambit (2)

items.summary: Stardate: 47225.7. Data's new dream subroutine causes him to experience nightmares which provide a unique insight into strange events that are occurring on board the Enterprise.
items.title: Phantasms

items.summary: Stardate: 47254.1. Lwaxana Troi collapses with a repressed memory related illness. Her only chance for survival is if Deanna can probe her subconscious and find out what is killing her. However, the secret Lwaxana holds is deeper than Deanna imagined.
items.title: Dark Page

items.summary: Stardate: 47304.2. While on a a diplomatic mission, Dr. Crusher and Picard are captured and imprisoned. As a result, they are linked together via a telepathic device.
items.title: Attached

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.7/Star.Trek.TNG.S07E09 - Force of Nature.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 47310.2. The Enterprise is drawn to a region of space where many starships have been mysteriously disabled. They soon learn that a brother and sister team has been working together to bring attention to the fact that frequent high-warp travel is damaging the very fabric of space/time.
items.title: Force of Nature

items.summary: Stardate: 47410.2. Data is disturbed by the claims of a woman who says she is Noonien Soong's ex-wife.
items.title: Inheritance

items.summary: Stardate: 47391.2. Worf returns from a Klingon competition to find that he is shifting through different realities.
items.title: Parallels

items.summary: Stardate: 47457.1. Riker is placed on a covert mission to find the missing starship he was once a member aboard, but the mission holds a secret that could destroy the peace treaty between the Federation and the Romulans.
items.title: The Pegasus

items.summary: Stardate: 47423.9. Worf's adoptive brother violates the Prime Directive to save an alien society whose planet is dying.
items.title: Homeward

items.summary: Stardate: Unknown. Dr. Crusher attends her grandmother's funeral, to find that she had been in romantic encounters with a mysterious man who had been haunting the Howard family women for generations.
items.title: Sub Rosa

items.summary: Stardate: 47566.7. Four young ensigns compete for a promotion that only one of them will receive. However, they are soon placed on a top secret mission that places some of their lives in danger.
items.title: Lower Decks

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.7/Star.Trek.TNG.S07E16 - Thine Own Self.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 47611.2. Data find himself mysteriously stranded on a planet with no recollection of who he is or how he arrived there. Soon he is accused of spreading a plague among the inhabitants. Troi takes the bridge officer's test in an attempt to gain the rank of Commander.
items.title: Thine Own Self

items.summary: Stardate: 47615.2. The Enterprise is slowly transformed into an ancient alien temple when Data discovers an alien archive full of information about an ancient culture. Shortly after opening the archive, Data becomes possessed with several different personalities.
items.title: Masks

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.7/Star.Trek.TNG.S07E18 - Eye of the Beholder.mkv
items.summary: Stardate: 47622.1. While investigating the mysterious suicide of a crew member, Troi and Worf begin to show romantic feeling towards one another.
items.title: Eye of the Beholder

items.summary: Stardate: 47653.2. Upon returning from an away mission, Picard and Data find the ship drifting in space, and the crew de-evolving into their animal ancestors.
items.title: Genesis

items.summary: Stardate: 47751.2. Under the terms of the new Federation/Cardassian alliance, Picard is ordered to evacuate a colony of native Americans, but protests from Wesley hamper the process. Wesley's destiny is finally revealed to him when the Traveler returns.
items.title: Journey's End

items.summary: Stardate: 47779.4. A disinterested Alexander must face his first Right of Ascension passage, but a mysterious warrior by the name of K'Mtar brings with him a disturbing request.
items.title: Firstborn

items.summary: Stardate: 47829.1. Picard tries to save his newly-discovered son from the retaliation of a vengeful Ferengi whose only son was killed by Picard buring the Battle of Maxia many years before.
items.title: Bloodlines

items.summary: Stardate: 47869.2. The Enterprise's computer systems starts having repeated malfunctions, leading the crew to believe that it may be evolving into a new life form.
items.title: Emergence

items.summary: Stardate: 47941.7. Fresh from Starfleet's Advanced Tactical Training course, Ro Laren is assigned to infiltrate the Maquis. However, over time she begins to sympathize with them, which forces her to choose between her loyalty to the Federation, and her new friends in the Maquis.
items.title: Preemptive Strike

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.7/Star.Trek.TNG.S07E25E26 - All Good Things.mkv
items.summary:
Stardate: 47988.0. Shortly after Picard is diagnosed with a long-term, potentially debilitating brain disorder, he starts experiencing bizarre shifts into three main time periods: 25 years into the future, a few days before the Enterprise-D is sent on its mission to Farpoint station, and the present. Picard realizes that Q is behind these shifts through time.

Stardate:  47988.1. After his encounter with Q, Picard assembles the senior staff, and wonders if Q is actually giving him a chance to save humanity by showing him that the spatial anomaly also exists in the past. As they talk, the ship reaches the Neutral Zone, then Picard returns to the future, where Beverly's ship is also on the edge of the Neutral Zone. He convinces a reluctant Worf to accompany the group into Klingon territory, and then travels to the past, where he orders the crew into the Devron system.
items.title: All Good Things...

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Star Trek TNG/Season.7/Star.Trek.TNG.S07E25E26 - All Good Things.mkv
items.title: Episode 26

items.summary: Stardate: 48315.6. While in pursuit of a Maquis ship in a region of space known as the 'Badlands', Captain Kathryn Janeway and her crew aboard Voyager and the Maquis ship are transported 70,000 light years from home into the uncharted region of the galaxy known as the Delta Quadrant.
items.title: Caretaker

items.summary: Stardate: Unknown. After being hit by the shockwave of a devastating planet-wide explosion, Voyager investigates. While on the surface, Janeway and Paris are accidentally 'shifted' one day into the past.
items.title: Time and Again

items.summary: Stardate: 48532.4. During an away mission in the search for dilithium crystals, Neelix is attacked and his lungs are surgically removed by a disease-ridden race of aliens known as the Vidiians. His only hope for survival is if the crew of Voyager can get them back.
items.title: Phage

items.summary: Stardate: 48546.2. In the search for omicron particles to boost the ship's energy supplies, Voyager inadvertently injures a space-faring life form.
items.title: The Cloud

items.summary: Stardate: 48579.4. The discovery of a wormhole leading to the Alpha Quadrant elates the crew, however, their only contact within range is a skeptical and paranoid Romulan.
items.title: Eye of the Needle

items.summary: Stardate: Unknown. Tom Paris is accused of a murder he claims he did not commit. His sentence is to re-live the last few moments of his victim's life every 14 hours through a memory transplant.
items.title: Ex Post Facto

items.summary: Stardate: 48623.5. While investigating an asteroid belt containing a new element, Harry Kim is pulled into a 'subspace vacuole' and switched with a dead body. Soon after the body is revived the crew learn that the asteroid belt is the graveyard of an alien culture that transports its dead in the belief that they evolve into a higher state of consciousness. Harry's appearance on the homeworld begins to raise questions about the existence of their afterlife.
items.title: Emanations

items.summary: Stardate: 48642.5. Harry Kim discovers advanced technology when a race of aliens known as the Sikarans offer shore leave to the crew of Voyager. This would send Voyager 40,000 light years closer to home, however, the Sikarians' "Canon of Laws" forbids them from sharing their technology with anyone.
items.title: Prime Factors

items.summary: Stardate: 48658.2. When stolen Federation technology is found on a severely damaged Kazon Nistrim ship, Seska becomes the prime suspect. The evidence is further reinforced when questions arise regarding her true heritage.
items.title: State of Flux

items.summary: Stardate: 48693.2. Harry Kim disappears from the holodeck during his holo-novel, "Beowulf." According to the characters, he died at the hands of a mystical beast known as "Grendel". When Chakotay and Tuvok also disappear, the Doctor is transferred to the holodeck to investigate.
items.title: Heroes and Demons

items.summary: Stardate: 48734.2. After Chakotay and Tuvok are injured in a shuttle accident, a non-corporeal life form begins to wreak havoc on Voyager by infiltrating the minds of the crew and altering the ship's systems one by one.
items.title: Cathexis

items.summary: Stardate: 48784.2. The Vidiians capture Paris, Torres and Durst while on an away mission. Torres is taken to a lab and 'split' into two people: one human, and one Klingon.
items.title: Faces

items.summary: Stardate: 48832.1. The man, who designed the weapon that destroyed all life on the moon of his home world, including that of his family, diagnoses Neelix with a fatal illness.
items.title: Jetrel

items.summary: Stardate: 48846.5. In order to bring some rebellious Maquis crewmembers into line, Tuvok gives them a Starfleet Academy crash course.
items.title: Learning Curve

items.summary: Stardate: 48975.1. After discovering a 1936 Ford truck from Earth floating in space Voyager discovers a series of cryo-statis chambers containing abductees from Earth during the 1930's, including Amelia Earhart and her navigator.
items.title: The 37's

items.summary: Stardate: 49005.3. A young Kazon trying to earn his name and place among his people kidnaps Chakotay.
items.title: Initiations

items.summary: Stardate: 48892.1. When the Doctor is activated during a Red Alert, he learns that the ship has been abandoned, and that only B'Elanna Torres and an injured Captain Janeway are left on board. Soon afterwards, Lt. Barclay appears and tells him that his entire time on Voyager is an elaborate simulation, and he's really a holo-engineer by the name of Zimmerman on Jupiter station in the Alpha Quadrant, who has been trapped on a holodeck for six hours. If he does not destroy Voyager's warp core and end the program soon he will die.
items.title: Projections
