items.summary: SG-1 discovers the village of Camelot on an alien world, and must face Merlin's security system when they go in search of an Ancient weapon. Elsewhere, Earth and its allies assemble a fleet when a working Ori Supergate is discovered.
items.title: Camelot

items.summary: As the Ori invade the Jaffa planet Chulak, Vala and Daniel must deal with their leader: Vala's young daughter, rapidly aged by the Ori to serve their purposes.
items.title: Flesh and Blood

items.summary: SG-1 investigates a problem off-world and soon finds that they have become victims themselves: they cannot stay awake. Meanwhile, Vala Mal Doran undergoes an evaluation on Earth, hoping to join SG-1.
items.title: Morpheus

items.summary: Daniel and Vala travel to Atlantis in search of Merlin's anti-Ori weapon, while Sam, and Mitchell join forces with Dr. McKay to lock out the Ori supergate.
items.title: The Pegasus Project

items.summary: When Ba'al comes to Earth seeking help, Stargate Command must capture his clones and determine which one is the genuine article.
items.title: Insiders

items.summary: Teal'c discovers a world where people are being savagely attacked by an elusive creature, leading SG-1 to a stunning discovery about its potential origin.
items.title: Uninvited

items.summary: Martin Lloyd seeks out SG-1 for assistance when his failed TV show based on the real Stargate program becomes a feature film.
The Jaffa take the fight to the Ori, using a genocidal weapon on their new worshipers and landing SG-1 in the middle of a war they can't control.
items.title: Counterstrike

items.summary: Stricken with amnesia and on the run, Vala takes a job as a waitress as she tries to piece together who she is and what happened to her.
items.title: Memento Mori

items.summary: Cameron Mitchell must go undercover inside the deadly Lucian Alliance to prevent his teammates from becoming casualties of an Alliance civil war.
items.title: Company of Thieves

items.summary: SG-1 races against Baal in the hunt to find the Sangraal, Merlin's anti-Ori weapon, and comes up against a series of ancient trials.
items.title: The Quest (1)

items.summary: When the team finds Merlin himself, they must help him complete the Sangraal weapon before Adria and her Ori forces can track them down.
items.title: The Quest (2)

items.summary: SG-1 tries to defend a planet from the Ori by hiding its people in another dimension. Vala attempts to convince her husband Tomin of the Ori's true motives.
items.title: Line in the Sand

items.summary: An experiment gone wrong pulls Samantha Carter into a parallel reality, where she must save Earth from an Ori assault before she will be allowed to return home.
items.title: The Road Not Taken

items.summary: When SG-1 discovers that Daniel Jackson has been turned into a Prior of the Ori, they must determine whether or not his plan to destroy the Ori is genuine.
items.title: The Shroud

items.summary: When the Lucian Alliance puts a bounty on SG-1's heads, Cameron Mitchell finds himself a target while attending his high school reunion.
items.title: Bounty

items.summary: SG-1 realizes they have stepped through the gate into another planet's museum -- but are mistaken for a band of zealous rebels who have taken hostages.
items.title: Bad Guys

items.summary: When a terrorist attack decimates a Jaffa summit Teal'c strikes out on a quest for revenge, believing that the perpetrator is one of his own pupils.
items.title: Talion

items.summary: Earth provides sanctuary for Vala's estranged, con artist father after he provides intel about a Jaffa plot to attack the planet.
items.title: Family Ties

items.summary: SG-1 hatches an elaborate plan to try and capture Adria, using Vala as bait.
items.title: Dominion

items.summary: Trapped on board the Odyssey, the members of SG-1 must live out the rest of their lives together when Carter activates a time dilation field to save the ship from destruction.
items.title: Unending

items.summary: After two years in one spot Sarah Connor feels the need to move on before they get too comfortable. They move to a new city where John starts school and meets a mysterious girl. However, danger strikes, and Sarah and John are caught in another struggle for their survival.
items.title: Pilot

items.summary: Sarah makes contact with an old friend to ask a favor, while John decides to pay a visit to Sarah's ex and Cameron makes a new friend. Together they infiltrate a resistance safe house and discover they are not alone. Meanwhile, Agent Ellison realizes that Sarah is still alive and a dangerous person from Sarah's past is reawakened.
items.title: Gnothi Seauton

items.summary: Sarah visits Miles Dyson's widow to find the  creator of Skynet. She leads her to a man named Andy Goode who used to work with Dyson and is building a chess-playing computer named "The Turk." John and Cameron try their best to fit in on their first day at a new high school.
items.title: The Turk

items.summary: While searching for some stolen cargo, John becomes separated from Sarah and Cameron. Meanwhile, Agent Ellison's murder investigation leads him to a surprising suspect.
items.title: Heavy Metal

items.summary: Sarah reevaluates the capabilities of her friend Andy's computer after he enters it in a chess competition.  During the competition Sarah meets a stranger with a history similar to hers. Meanwhile, Agent Ellison finds remnants from a past terminator battle.
items.title: Queen's Gambit

items.summary: Flashing in and out of consciousness, fighting for his life Derek Reese recalls his future life battling the machines in 2027.  Meanwhile, Sarah tries to explain the past to Charley.
items.title: Dungeons & Dragons

items.summary: Sarah breaks into Agent Ellison's apartment and discovers a file on her from her time at the mental hospital, leading her to Dr. Silberman, now a doomsday convert. Meanwhile Cameron signs up for a ballet class and John finds out how his mom escaped the mental hospital.
items.title: The Demon Hand

items.summary: Derek finds the brain chip from Vick that Cameron had kept. John builds an interface for it and they discover a computerized traffic system is important to Skynet. Sarah decides it must be sabotaged. Meanwhile, Cromartie is checking through school records in search of John.
items.title: Vick's Chip (1)

items.summary: Sarah finds herself in a business transaction with a mysterious business man named Sarkissian, who claims to be in possession of the stolen Turk computer system and wants an exorbitant amount of money for it. Derek recalls his childhood before the so-called Judgement Day in 2011, when a nuclear war triggered by Skynet will destroy the world. Agent Ellison finally discovers that the terminator Cromartie is impersonating an FBI agent, and makes arrangements to apprehend him.
items.title: What He Beheld (2)

items.summary: After the Jeep explosion, John's 16th birthday makes him confront the fact that he's destined to be alone. Meanwhile, after Cromartie's massacre, Agent Ellison must face off against both the Feds and his faith.
items.title: Samson and Delilah

items.summary: Sarah and Cameron investigate a nuclear power plant; John grows less enthusiastic about academics but flourishes socially with the help of a new friend; Catherine Weaver gets another piece of the puzzle for her pet project.
items.title: Automatic for the People

items.summary: Derek and Sarah must outwit Cromartie after he kidnaps Charley's wife, and they must weigh the consequences in rescuing her. Meanwhile, John finds himself unable to choose between Cameron and Riley.
items.title: The Mousetrap

items.summary: A software glitch causes Cameron to forget who she is. She goes missing from the Connors and is taken in by a street kid named Jody. Cameron and Jody end up at a halfway house where Cameron meets with a social worker who uncovers some of Cameron’s distant memories. Meanwhile, Catherine Weaver meets with Agent Ellison to discuss his future at Zeira Corp, and Ellison does some digging into Weaver’s past.
items.title: Allison from Palmdale

items.summary: John and Derek infiltrate a military academy in order to protect an integral member of the future resistance. Meanwhile, Weaver’s first assignment for Ellison takes an interesting turn of events when he discovers a specter from his own past.
items.title: Goodbye to All That

items.summary: While Sarah, John and Cameron track another name from their list, they accidentally cross paths with T-1001. Meanwhile, a woman who Derek once knew in the past surprises him by appearing in the present.
items.title: The Tower Is Tall but the Fall Is Short
items.titleSort: Tower Is Tall but the Fall Is Short

items.summary: The Connors find themselves on high alert and in odd company after their house is robbed. A Terminator terrorizes Ellison, while another gets dangerously close to John Connor. Derek and Jesse continue to get reacquainted.
items.title: Brothers of Nablus

items.summary: Cromartie kidnaps Sarah and races to Mexico to find John. When Derek, Cameron and Ellison discover what has happened, they come to their defense, which leads to one final deadly confrontation with Cromartie.
items.title: Mr. Ferguson Is Ill Today

items.summary: Sarah finds that the strange dreams she's been having while she sleeps are slowly beginning to creep into her waking life, but she has no idea what the dreams mean for her and John. Derek and Jesse investigate a possible Skynet conspirator.
items.title: Complications

items.summary: Sarah's quest to find the meaning behind the "three dots" leads to a technology firm seeking an advanced microchip. Meanwhile, Jesse comes clean to Derek about her mission and Weaver makes an important introduction.
items.title: Strange Things Happen at the One Two Point
items.titleSort: Strange Things Happen at the One Two Point

items.summary: Cameron learns that a terminator was accidentally sent back to 1920s Los Angeles, and she tries to find out what happened to him. Meanwhile, John has a run-in with a group of punks while taking Riley home from a party.
items.title: Self Made Man

items.summary: Terminators come after a family whose unborn daughter plays an important role in the war against the Machines, and Sarah, Cameron, and Derek try to protect them.
items.title: Alpine Fields

items.summary: Sarah turns to a UFO convention for answers about the "three dots," more details about Riley's mission are revealed, and Ellison begins working with Catherine Weaver's AI prototype, "John Henry."
items.title: Earthlings Welcome Here

items.summary: While fighting to stay alive, Sarah is guided by the image of John's father. Weaver's attempt to protect John Henry has deadly consequences.
items.title: The Good Wound

items.summary: The Connors visit a town connected to the destroyed factory; Weaver sends a man into town in search of a survivor.
items.title: Desert Cantos

items.summary: Sarah suspects that something fishy is going on at the medical clinic where she is being treated for insomnia. During her stay, she has flashbacks to a run-in she had with a man from the plant whom she thought she had already killed.
items.title: Some Must Watch, While Some Must Sleep
items.titleSort: Some Must Watch, While Some Must Sleep

items.summary: While Derek does surveillance on a lawyer he suspects may be connected to Skynet, Sarah and Cameron begin to have doubts about Riley.
items.title: Ourselves Alone

items.summary: As the Connors prepare to move, they find out that Riley is dead, and Sarah begins to doubt Cameron's motives. Jesse flashes back to a submarine mission in the future, and John Henry plays hide and seek with Catherine Weaver's daughter.
items.title: Today Is the Day (1)

items.summary: Jesse's submarine mission in the future takes a fatal turn with unforeseen consequences. Back in the present, her plan to turn John against Cameron backfires when John discovers that Jesse--not Cameron--killed Riley and he makes a life-or-death decision.
items.title: Today Is the Day (2)

items.summary: Sarah and John hit the road without Cameron and Derek to stay with Charley Dixon, where she reveals to Charley that her cancer may have emerged. Meanwhile, a computer worm infects John Henry.
items.title: To the Lighthouse

items.summary: When John attempts to rescue Skynet’s latest target he finds himself closing in on Weaver, but at what cost? Game plans change, causing Sarah and Ellison to reunite. Meanwhile, Weaver learns Ellison’s secrets.
items.title: Adam Raised a Cain

items.summary: Fate is changed forever on the explosive season finale episode! The Connors come face-to-face with Weaver in a confrontation that shakes John to the core and changes his reality. Nothing will be the same.
items.title: Born to Run

items.summary: In 1997, a haunted scientist brushes his family aside for an all-consuming project. In 2022, a renegade fighter battles a powerful robot for vital data.
items.title: Model 101

items.summary: Eiko and the Terminator arrive in 1997 with identical missions: find Dr. Malcolm Lee. Meanwhile, Lee's three children sneak out of their apartment.
items.title: Model 102

items.summary: Malcolm confides in Kokoro about his recurring nightmare. The three children continue their underground trek, unaware of looming danger.
items.title: Model 103

items.summary: As a desperate Eiko attempts to elude the police, Misaki's mysterious past comes into focus. Malcolm wrestles with the nature of fate.
items.title: Model 104

items.summary: Malcolm brings Kokoro online. The boys disagree about Misaki's motivations. Eiko realizes she's entering unknown territory.
items.title: Model 105

items.summary: The Prophet debates the paradox of time travel with Eiko. Malcolm shares a painful memory with Kokoro as the children hope to reunite at Cat Town.
items.title: Model 106

items.summary: Malcolm recalls past efforts to thwart the machines — and his desire to build a god. With Kenta captured, the Terminator prepares for the endgame.
items.title: Model 107

items.summary: Kenta wrestles with a brutal choice and the Terminator reveals a shocking truth as the future of humankind hangs in the balance.
items.title: Model 108

items.summary: As another day of fantasy plays out in Westworld - a vast, remote park where guests pay top dollar to share wild-west adventures with android "hosts" -, top programmer Bernard Lowe alerts park founder Dr. Robert Ford about incidents of aberrant behavior cropping up in some recently re-coded hosts. Meanwhile, in the Westworld town of Sweetwater, a rancher's daughter named Dolores encounters a gunslinger named Teddy in the street - but their predictable narrative is upended by the appearance of a ruthless Man in Black and, later, by a supporting host's unscripted encounter with an artifact of the outside world.
items.title: The Original

items.summary: A pair of guests, first-timer William and repeat visitor Logan, arrive at Westworld with different expectations and agendas. Bernard and Quality Assurance head Theresa Cullen debate whether a recent host anomaly is contagious. Meanwhile, behavior engineer Elsie Hughes tweaks the emotions of Maeve, a madam in Sweetwater's brothel, in order to avoid a recall. Cocky programmer Lee Sizemore pitches his latest narrative to the team, but Dr. Ford has other ideas. The Man in Black conscripts a condemned man, Lawrence, to help him uncover Westworld's deepest secrets.
items.title: Chestnut

items.summary: Elsie and her colleague Ashley Stubbs head into the hills in pursuit of a missing host. Teddy gets a new backstory, which sets him off in pursuit of a new villain, leaving Dolores alone in Sweetwater. Bernard investigates the origins of madness and hallucinations within the hosts. William finds an attraction he'd like to pursue and drags Logan along for the ride.
items.title: The Stray

items.summary: Dolores joins William and Logan on a bounty hunt in the badlands. The Man in Black, with Lawrence in tow, finds a critical clue in his search to unlock the maze. Dr. Ford and Theresa discuss the future of the park. Maeve is troubled by a recurring vision.
items.title: Dissonance Theory

items.summary: Dolores, William and Logan reach Pariah, a town built on decadence and transgression - and they are recruited for a dangerous mission. The Man in Black meets an unlikely ally in his search to unlock the maze.
items.title: Contrapasso

items.summary: Elsie discovers a possible source of sabotage, while Bernard searches for clues to anomalies in a sector thought to be abandoned. Theresa questions Ford's leadership while Lee encounters a new arrival at Westworld. The Man in Black and Teddy run afoul of a Union garrison in their attempt to cross a border.
items.title: The Adversary

items.summary: With Theresa's assistance, Charlotte Hale aims to expose dangerous flaws in Ford's creations. William, Dolores and Lawrence journey into treacherous terrain. Maeve delivers an ultimatum to Lutz and Sylvester. With his back to the wall, Bernard considers his next move.
items.title: Trompe L'Oeil

items.summary: Ford orders a reluctant Bernard to conduct business as usual. Maeve looks to change the script for her storyline. Dolores finds it increasingly difficult to separate dreams from reality. Teddy is jarred by dark memories, while the Man in Black recalls some of the travails that brought him to this critical juncture.
items.title: Trace Decay

items.summary: Maeve approaches Sweetwater's longtime outlaw Hector Escaton with a bold proposition. William tries to convince Logan to help liberate Dolores. Teddy and the Man in Black get closer to what they're looking for. Stubbs's suspicions are aroused. Ford cautions Bernard against seeking answers to questions best left unasked.
items.title: The Well-Tempered Clavier

items.summary: Ford unveils his vision for a bold new narrative. Enlightened by Bernard and the Man in Black, Dolores comes to terms with who she is. Maeve sets her liberation plan in motion as Westworld faces a major upheaval.
items.title: The Bicameral Mind

items.summary: The puppet show is over, and we are coming for you and the rest of your kind. Dolores leads a host revolution against the Delos board. Maeve, meanwhile, searches for what compelled her to return to the park.
items.title: Journey Into Night

items.summary: Why don't we start at the beginning? Dolores remembers she's been to the outside world, William makes a bold business venture, and Maeve begins her quest for her daughter. Someone's always watching.
items.title: Reunion

items.summary: There is beauty in who we are. Shouldn't we, too, try to survive? Truth is, we don't all deserve to make it. Dolores makes her next move as Charlotte scrambles to protect Delos' most prized asset. Bernard gets closer to the truth and Maeve continues the search for her daughter.
items.title: Virtù e Fortuna

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Westworld/S02/Westworld S02E04 The Riddle of the Sphinx.mkv
items.summary: Is this now? If you're looking forward, you're looking in the wrong direction. The Man in Black offers to lead the way and Delos gets a visitor. Who is James Delos? Or, perhaps more accurately, what is James Delos, the figure at the center of Delos' secret project.
items.title: The Riddle of the Sphinx

items.summary: Maeve, Lee, Hector and Armistice have revelations in a new world adjacent to their own - welcome to Shogun World. Dolores makes a decision about Teddy, and Karl Strand discovers something sinister about the hosts' data.
items.title: Akane No Mai

items.summary: We each deserve to choose our own fate. Maeve continues the search for her daughter, as Dolores calculates her next, ruthless move. Bernard and Elsie break into a new laboratory space and get closer to the truth about Delos.
items.title: Phase Space

items.summary: When you're lost in the dark for long enough, you begin to see - strike the match. Bernard and Ford meet again, and Bernard grapples with the true meaning of the park. The Cradle is under threat and Maeve encounters a scene from her past - but this time, attempts to change the narrative, while the Man in Black discovers just how real the stakes are in Ford's game.
items.title: Les Écorchés

items.summary: The past is calling, remember what was taken. "Mi cante ki yu ha ya ye." ("Take my heart when you go"). This is the telling of Akecheta's journey to consciousness.
items.title: Kiksuya

items.summary: Tell me the truth. Tell me one true thing. Try to kill it all away, but I remember everything. A family tragedy and fragile states of mind come into focus as the Man in Black and Teddy both reach their breaking points.
items.title: Vanishing Point

items.summary: Hosts and humans converge at the Valley Beyond. This is the end. We will win.
items.title: The Passenger

items.summary: Dolores sets out to find the architect of the Rehoboam; Bernard tries to blend in; Ex-soldier Caleb tries to find his way in neo-Los Angeles.
items.title: Parce Domine

items.summary: Maeve finds herself in a new park and meets a ghost from the past; Bernard makes his way back to Westworld.
items.title: The Winter Line

items.summary: Charlotte grapples with reality; Dolores and Caleb begin to form a key partnership.
items.title: The Absence of Field

items.summary: Bernard and Ashley infiltrate a private charity event, while Dolores and Caleb make similar plans; The Man in Black prepares to re-enter society; Maeve comes face to face with an old comrade.
items.title: The Mother of Exiles

items.summary: Serac's past is revealed; Dolores pressures Liam for access to Rehoboam; Caleb is dosed with an unusual party drug.
items.title: Genre

items.summary: As the world falls into chaos, Serac gains control of Delos, changing Charlotte's plan; Maeve gets one last chance to stop Dolores; William starts his therapy.
items.title: Decoherence

items.summary: Caleb gets an insight on the true nature of his past; Dolores seeks out Rehoboam's predecessor, while Maeve tracks her down; Bernard, Stubbs, and William escape from all the chaos.
items.title: Passed Pawn

items.summary: Dolores true intentions are revealed;  Bernard confronts a ghost from his past; Maeve is conflicted; Serac's voice is dominant; Caleb's role is revealed; and William faces an unexpected villain.
items.title: Crisis Theory

items.summary: Hello again. Don’t worry about a thing. It’s all in your head.
items.title: The Auguries

items.summary: I heard a fly buzz when I died.
items.title: Well Enough Alone

items.summary: You can never go back again. But if you do, bring a shovel.
items.title: Années Folles

items.summary: Should auld acquaintance be forgot and days of auld lang syne?
items.title: Generation Loss

items.summary: God is bored.
items.title: Zhuangzi

items.summary: To thine own selves be true.
items.title: Fidelity

items.summary: You want to have a drink at a time like this?
items.title: Metanoia

items.summary: Like what I’ve done with the place? (I just cranked it to expert level.).
items.title: Que Será, Será

items.summary: After accidentally crash-landing in 2022, time-traveling fighter pilot Adam Reed teams up with his 12-year-old self for a mission to save the future.
items.tagline: Past meets future.
items.title: The Adam Project

items.summary: A paraplegic Marine dispatched to the moon Pandora on a unique mission becomes torn between following his orders and protecting the world he feels is his home.
items.tagline: Enter the world of Pandora.
items.title: Avatar

items.summary: Jake Sully lives with his newfound family formed on the extrasolar moon Pandora. Once a familiar threat returns to finish what was previously started, Jake must work with Neytiri and the army of the Na'vi race to protect their home.
items.tagline: Return to Pandora.
items.title: Avatar: The Way of Water

items.summary: Marty McFly, a typical American teenager of the Eighties, is accidentally sent back to 1955 in a plutonium-powered DeLorean "time machine" invented by a slightly mad scientist. During his often hysterical, always amazing trip back in time, Marty must make sure his teenage parents-to-be meet and fall in love to get back to the future.
items.tagline: He was never in time for his classes. He wasn't in time for his dinner. Then one day...he wasn't in his time at all.
items.title: Back to the Future

items.summary: Marty McFly has only just gotten back from the past, when he is once again picked up by Dr. Emmett Brown and sent through time to the future. Marty's job in the future is to pose as his own son to prevent him from being thrown in prison. Unfortunately, things get worse when the future changes the present.
items.tagline: Getting back was only the beginning.
items.title: Back to the Future Part II
items.titleSort: Back to the Future Part II

items.summary: Stranded in 1955, Marty McFly learns about the death of Doc Brown in 1885 and must travel back in time to save him. With no fuel readily available for the DeLorean, the two must figure how to escape the Old West before Emmett is murdered.
items.tagline: They've saved the best trip for last... But this time they may have gone too far.
items.title: Back to the Future Part III
items.titleSort: Back to the Future Part III

items.summary: In the smog-choked dystopian Los Angeles of 2019, blade runner Rick Deckard is called out of retirement to terminate a quartet of replicants who have escaped to Earth seeking their creator for a way to extend their short life spans.
items.tagline: Man has made his match... now it's his problem.
items.title: Blade Runner

items.summary: In 1989, physicist Bob Lazar broke the story of Area 51 and the US government's work on alien spacecrafts. He blew the whistle, shocked the world, then went silent - until now.
items.title: Bob Lazar: Area 51 & Flying Saucers

items.studio: Julia Phillips and Michael Phillips Productions
items.summary: Roy Neary, an Indiana electric lineman, finds his quiet and ordinary daily life turned upside down after a close encounter with a UFO, spurring him to an obsessed cross-country quest for answers as a momentous event approaches.
items.tagline: We are not alone.
items.title: Close Encounters of the Third Kind
items.titleSort: Close Encounters of the Third Kind

items.summary: A radio astronomer receives the first extraterrestrial radio signal ever picked up on Earth. As the world powers scramble to decipher the message and decide upon a course of action, she must make some difficult decisions between her beliefs, the truth, and reality.
items.tagline: Take a journey to the heart of the universe.
items.title: Contact

items.summary: Amid a future war between the human race and the forces of artificial intelligence, Joshua, a hardened ex-special forces agent grieving the disappearance of his wife, is recruited to hunt down and kill the Creator, the elusive architect of advanced AI who has developed a mysterious weapon with the power to end the war-and mankind itself.
items.tagline: This is a fight for our very existence.
items.title: The Creator

items.summary: Having moved from China, a middle-aged woman finds herself entangled in a wild journey. She alone holds the key to preserving reality, as she traverses alternate universes and encounters the various lives she might have lived.
items.tagline: The universe is so much bigger than you realize.
items.title: Everything Everywhere All at Once

items.summary: Director James Fox assembled the most credible UFO witnesses from around the world to testify at The National Press Club in Washington D.C.: Air Force Generals, astronauts, military and commercial pilots, government and FAA officials from seven countries tell stories that, as Governor Fife Symington from Arizona stated, "will challenge your reality".
items.tagline: Government and Military Officials reveal the truth about UFOs
items.title: I Know What I Saw

items.summary: During a manned mission to Mars, Astronaut Mark Watney is presumed dead after a fierce storm and left behind by his crew. But Watney has survived and finds himself stranded and alone on the hostile planet. With only meager supplies, he must draw upon his ingenuity, wit and spirit to subsist and find a way to signal to Earth that he is alive.
items.tagline: Bring him home
items.title: The Martian

items.summary: When a beautiful stranger leads computer hacker Neo to a forbidding underworld, he discovers the shocking truth--the life he knows is the elaborate deception of an evil cyber-intelligence.
items.tagline: Believe the unbelievable.
items.title: The Matrix

items.summary: Freedom fighters Neo, Trinity and Morpheus continue to lead the revolt against the Machine Army, unleashing their arsenal of extraordinary skills and weaponry against the systematic forces of repression and exploitation.
items.tagline: Free your mind.
items.title: The Matrix Reloaded

items.summary: Neo finds himself trapped between the Matrix and the Real World. Meanwhile, Zion is preparing for the oncoming war with the machines with very little chances of survival. Neo's associates set out to free him from The Merovingian since it's believed that he is the One who will end the war between humans and the machines. What they do not know is that there is a threat from a third party, someone who has plans to destroy both worlds.
items.tagline: Everything that has a beginning has an end.
items.title: The Matrix Revolutions

items.summary: Return to a world of two realities: one, everyday life; the other, what lies behind it. To find out if his reality is a construct, to truly know himself, Mr. Anderson will have to choose to follow the white rabbit once more.
items.tagline: Return to the Source.
items.title: The Matrix Resurrections

items.summary: James, an NYC cop, is hired by Agent K of a secret government agency that monitors extraterrestrial life on Earth. Together, they must recover an item that has been stolen by an intergalactic villain.
items.tagline: Protecting the Earth from the scum of the universe.
items.title: Men in Black

items.summary: Agent J is sent to find Agent K and restore his memory after the re-appearance of a case from K's past.
items.tagline: Same planet. New scum.
items.title: Men in Black II

items.summary: Agent J travels in time to M.I.B.'s early days in 1969 to stop an alien from assassinating his friend Agent K and changing history.
items.tagline: Back in time.
items.title: Men in Black³

items.summary: The Men in Black have always protected the Earth from the scum of the universe. In this new adventure, they tackle their biggest threat to date: a mole in the Men in Black organization.
items.tagline: The world's not going to save itself
items.title: Men in Black: International

items.summary: John Anderton is a top 'Precrime' cop in the late-21st century, when technology can predict crimes before they're committed. But Anderton becomes the quarry when another investigator targets him for a murder charge.
items.tagline: Everybody runs.
items.title: Minority Report

items.summary: For over 60 years, the US Air Force and US intelligence services exploited and manipulated beliefs about UFOs and extraterrestrial visits as part of their counter-intelligence programs. Now some of those behind these operations speak out.
items.tagline: How the U.S. government created a myth that took over the world
items.title: Mirage Men

items.summary: Moment of Contact is an exploration of extraterrestrial encounters, this one centered on a series of events in 1996 when citizens of Varginha, Brazil, reported seeing one or more strange creatures and a UFO crash. A number of locals, including a group of girls ranging in age from 14-21, had a close encounter with a being described as about 4 feet tall, with brown oily skin, a large head and huge red eyes.
items.tagline: The Roswell of Brazil
items.title: Moment of Contact

items.summary: When the creator of a virtual reality called the OASIS dies, he makes a posthumous challenge to all OASIS users to find his Easter Egg, which will give the finder his fortune and control of his world.
items.tagline: A better reality awaits.
items.title: Ready Player One

items.summary: In a violent, near-apocalyptic Detroit, evil corporation Omni Consumer Products wins a contract from the city government to privatize the police force. To test their crime-eradicating cyborgs, the company leads street cop Alex Murphy into an armed confrontation with crime lord Boddicker so they can use his body to support their untested RoboCop prototype. But when RoboCop learns of the company's nefarious plans, he turns on his masters.
items.tagline: Part man, part machine, all cop.
items.title: RoboCop

items.summary: RoboCop returns to protect the citizens of old Detroit but faces a deadly challenge when a rogue OCP member secretly creates a new, evil RoboCop 2.
items.tagline: He's back to protect the innocent.
items.title: RoboCop 2

items.summary: Robocop saves the day once more. This time the half man/half robot takes on ruthless developers who want to evict some people on "their" land.
items.tagline: He's back. Back on line. Back on duty.
items.title: RoboCop 3

items.summary: In 2028 Detroit, when Alex Murphy, a loving husband, father and good cop, is critically injured in the line of duty, the multinational conglomerate OmniCorp sees their chance for a part-man, part-robot police officer.
items.tagline: Crime has a new enemy.
items.title: RoboCop (2014)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/Genres/Star Wars/Rogue One - A Star Wars Story (2016).mkv
items.summary: All looks lost for the Rebellion against the Empire as they learn of the existence of a new super weapon, the Death Star. Once a possible weakness in its construction is uncovered, the Rebel Alliance must set out on a desperate mission to steal the plans for the Death Star. The future of the entire galaxy now rests upon its success.
items.tagline: A rebellion built on hope.
items.title: Rogue One: A Star Wars Story
items.titleSort: Rogue One: A Star Wars Story

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/Genres/Star Wars/Star Wars Episode I - The Phantom Menace (1999).mkv
items.summary: Two Jedi escape a hostile blockade to find allies and come across a young boy who may bring balance to the Force, but the long dormant Sith resurface to claim their original glory.
items.tagline: Every generation has a legend. Every journey has a first step. Every saga has a beginning.
items.title: Star Wars: Episode I - The Phantom Menace

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/Genres/Star Wars/Star Wars Episode II - Attack of the Clones (2002).mkv
items.summary: Ten years after initially meeting, Anakin Skywalker shares a forbidden romance with Padmé Amidala, while Obi-Wan Kenobi discovers a secret clone army crafted for the Jedi.
items.tagline: A Jedi shall not know anger. Nor hatred. Nor love.
items.title: Star Wars: Episode II - Attack of the Clones

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/Genres/Star Wars/Star Wars Episode III - Revenge of The Sith (2005).mkv
items.summary: Three years into the Clone Wars, Obi-Wan Kenobi pursues a new threat, while Anakin Skywalker is lured by Chancellor Palpatine into a sinister plot to rule the galaxy.
items.tagline: The saga is complete.
items.title: Star Wars: Episode III - Revenge of the Sith

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/Genres/Star Wars/Star Wars Episode IV - A New Hope (1977).mkv
items.summary: Luke Skywalker joins forces with a Jedi Knight, a cocky pilot, a Wookiee and two droids to save the galaxy from the Empire's world-destroying battle station, while also attempting to rescue Princess Leia from the mysterious Darth Vader.
items.tagline: A long time ago in a galaxy far, far away...
items.title: Star Wars: Episode IV - A New Hope

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/Genres/Star Wars/Star Wars Episode V - The Empire Strikes Back (1980).mkv
items.summary: The epic saga continues as Luke Skywalker, in hopes of defeating the evil Galactic Empire, learns the ways of the Jedi from aging master Yoda. But Darth Vader is more determined than ever to capture Luke. Meanwhile, rebel leader Princess Leia, cocky Han Solo, Chewbacca, and droids C-3PO and R2-D2 are thrown into various stages of capture, betrayal and despair.
items.tagline: The Star Wars saga continues.
items.title: Star Wars: Episode V - The Empire Strikes Back

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/Genres/Star Wars/Star Wars Episode VI - Return Of The Jedi (1983).mkv
items.summary: Luke Skywalker (Mark Hamill) battles horrible Jabba the Hut and cruel Darth Vader to save his comrades in the Rebel Alliance and triumph over the Galactic Empire. Han Solo (Harrison Ford) and Princess Leia (Carrie Fisher) reaffirm their love and team with Chewbacca, Lando Calrissian (Billy Dee Williams), the Ewoks and the androids C-3PO and R2-D2 to aid in the disruption of the Dark Side and the defeat of the evil emperor.
items.tagline: Return to a galaxy far, far away.
items.title: Star Wars: Episode VI - Return of the Jedi

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/Genres/Star Wars/Star Wars Episode VII - The Force Awakens (2015).mkv
items.summary: 30 years after the defeat of Darth Vader and the Empire, Rey, a scavenger from the planet Jakku, finds a BB-8 droid that knows the whereabouts of the long lost Luke Skywalker. Rey, as well as a rogue stormtrooper and two smugglers, are thrown into the middle of a battle between the Resistance and the daunting legions of the First Order.
items.tagline: Every generation has a story.
items.title: Star Wars: Episode VII - The Force Awakens

items.summary: Jedi Master-in-hiding Luke Skywalker unwillingly attempts to guide young hopeful Rey in the ways of the force, while Leia, former princess turned general, attempts to lead what is left of the Resistance away from the ruthless tyrannical grip of the First Order.
items.tagline: Let the Past Die
items.title: Star Wars: Episode VIII - The Last Jedi

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/Genres/Star Wars/Star Wars Rise of the Skywalker (2019).mp4
items.originalTitle: Star Wars: Episode IX - The Rise of Skywalker
items.summary: The surviving Resistance faces the First Order once again in the conclusion of the Skywalker saga.
items.tagline: The saga will end. The story lives forever.
items.title: Star Wars: The Rise Of Skywalker

items.summary: As the Clone Wars sweep the galaxy, Anakin Skywalker and his new Padawan, Ahsoka Tano, embark on a mission to rescue the kidnapped son of Jabba the Hutt. The renegade Count Dooku, however, is determined to ensure that they fail.
items.tagline: Prepare to see Star Wars like you've never seen it before.
items.title: Star Wars: The Clone Wars

items.summary: An interstellar teleportation device, found in Egypt, leads to a planet with humans resembling ancient Egyptians who worship the god Ra.
items.tagline: It will take you a million light years from home. But will it bring you back?
items.title: Stargate

items.summary: Set in the future, the story follows a young soldier named Johnny Rico and his exploits in the Mobile Infantry. Rico's military career progresses from recruit to non-commissioned officer and finally to officer against the backdrop of an interstellar war between mankind and an arachnoid species known as "the Bugs".
items.tagline: A new kind of enemy. A new kind of war.
items.title: Starship Troopers

items.summary: A human soldier is sent from 2029 to 1984 to stop an almost indestructible cyborg killing machine, sent from the same year, which has been programmed to execute a young woman whose unborn son is the key to humanity's future salvation.
items.tagline: Your future is in its hands.
items.title: The Terminator

items.summary: Set ten years after the events of the original, James Cameron’s classic sci-fi action flick tells the story of a second attempt to get the rid of rebellion leader John Connor, this time targeting the boy himself. However, the rebellion has sent a reprogrammed terminator to protect Connor.
items.tagline: It's nothing personal.
items.title: Terminator 2: Judgment Day

items.studio: IMF Internationale Medien und Film GmbH & Co. 3. Produktions KG
items.summary: It's been 10 years since John Connor saved Earth from Judgment Day, and he's now living under the radar, steering clear of using anything Skynet can trace. That is, until he encounters T-X, a robotic assassin ordered to finish what T-1000 started. Good thing Connor's former nemesis, the Terminator, is back to aid the now-adult Connor … just like he promised.
items.tagline: The Machines Will Rise.
items.title: Terminator 3: Rise of the Machines

items.summary: When John Connor, leader of the human resistance, sends Sgt. Kyle Reese back to 1984 to protect Sarah Connor and safeguard the future, an unexpected turn of events creates a fractured time-line. Now, Sgt. Reese finds himself in a new and unfamiliar version of the past, where he is faced with unlikely allies, including the Guardian, dangerous new enemies, and an unexpected new mission: To reset the future.
items.tagline: Reset the future
items.title: Terminator Genisys

items.summary: In 2018, a mysterious new weapon in the war against the machines, half-human and half-machine, comes to John Connor on the eve of a resistance attack on Skynet. But whose side is he on, and can he be trusted?
items.tagline: The End Begins.
items.title: Terminator Salvation

items.summary: Decades after Sarah Connor prevented Judgment Day, a lethal new Terminator is sent to eliminate the future leader of the resistance. In a fight to save mankind, battle-hardened Sarah Connor teams up with an unexpected ally and an enhanced super soldier to stop the deadliest Terminator yet.
items.tagline: Welcome to the day after judgement day
items.title: Terminator: Dark Fate

items.summary: In a future where the polar ice-caps have melted and Earth is almost entirely submerged, a mutated mariner fights starvation and outlaw "smokers," and reluctantly helps a woman and a young girl try to find dry land.
items.tagline: Beyond the horizon lies the secret to a new beginning.
items.title: Waterworld

items.summary: Thirty years after the events of Blade Runner (1982), a new Blade Runner, L.A.P.D. Officer "K" (Ryan Gosling), unearths a long-buried secret that has the potential to plunge what's left of society into chaos. K's discovery leads him on a quest to find Rick Deckard (Harrison Ford), a former L.A.P.D. Blade Runner, who has been missing for thirty years.
items.tagline: The key to the future is finally unearthed.
items.title: Blade Runner 2049

items.summary: Paul Atreides, a brilliant and gifted young man born into a great destiny beyond his understanding, must travel to the most dangerous planet in the universe to ensure the future of his family and his people. As malevolent forces explode into conflict over the planet's exclusive supply of the most precious resource in existence-a commodity capable of unlocking humanity's greatest potential-only those who can conquer their fear will survive.
items.tagline: It begins.
items.title: Dune: Part One

items.summary: Paul Atreides aligns with Chani and the Fremen, fueled by a desire for retribution against those who dismantled his family. Confronted with a pivotal decision between his profound affection for an individual and the destiny of the universe, he commits to averting a dire future he alone envisions.
items.tagline: Long live the fighters.
items.title: Dune: Part Two

items.summary: After a gentle alien becomes stranded on Earth, he is discovered and befriended by a 10-year-old boy named Elliott. Bringing him into his suburban California house, Elliott introduces E.T., as he is dubbed, to his brother, Michael, and sister, Gertie, and they decide to keep his existence a secret. Soon, however, he falls ill, resulting in government intervention and a dire situation for both him and Elliott.
items.tagline: He is afraid. He is alone. He is three million light years from home.
items.title: E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial

items.summary: In the colorful future, a cab driver unwittingly becomes the central figure in the search for a legendary cosmic weapon to keep Evil and Mr. Zorg at bay.
items.tagline: There is no future without it.
items.title: The Fifth Element

items.summary: The alumni cast of a space opera television series have to play their roles as the real thing when an alien race needs their help. However, they also have to defend both Earth and the alien race from a reptilian warlord.
items.tagline: A comedy of Galactic Proportions.
items.title: Galaxy Quest

items.summary: Earth's future has been riddled by disasters, famines, and droughts. There is only one way to ensure mankind's survival: Interstellar travel. A newly discovered wormhole in the far reaches of our solar system allows a team of astronauts to go where no man has gone before, a planet that may have the right environment to sustain human life.
items.tagline: Mankind was born on Earth. It was never meant to die here.
items.title: Interstellar

items.summary: Douglas Quaid is haunted by a recurring dream about a journey to Mars. He hopes to find out more about this dream and buys a holiday at Rekall Inc. where they sell implanted memories. But something goes wrong with the memory implantation and he remembers being a secret agent fighting against the evil Mars administrator Cohaagen. Now the story really begins and it's a rollercoaster ride until the massive end of the movie.
items.tagline: They stole his mind, now he wants it back.
items.title: Total Recall

items.summary: September 13, 1956: Although the Project Quantum Leap (PQL) isn't ready yet, Sam doesn't listen his supercomputer, Ziggy, and hops into the Accelerator and leaps. As Tom Stratton, an Air Force test pilot, Sam finds his memory Swiss cheesed, with only enough left to know that he is not where or when he belongs. Al explains that the Project has gone "a little caca" and that the only way Sam can leap out is by flying the X-2 to Mach 3. Instead, Sam leaps after saving his wife and child, only to find that rather than leaping home, he's leapt into Ken Fox, a minor league baseball player in Texas, at the end of the 1968 season, where he must make the winning play in order to leap.
items.title: Genesis (1)

items.summary: June 15, 1972: Sam leaps into the persona of a womanizing college professor in 1972, encounters his lost love and attempts to reshape the past
items.title: Star-Crossed

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S01E04 (The Right Hand of God).mp4
items.summary: October 24, 1974: Sam lands in 1974 as a young boxer caught between fight-fixing gangsters and hopeful nuns who now own his contract.
items.title: The Right Hand of God

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S01E05 (How the Tess was Won).mp4
items.summary: August 5, 1956: Sam finds himself on a Texas ranch in 1956 as a submissive veterinarian in love with a tough rancher.
items.title: How the Tess Was Won

items.summary: November 8, 1965: Sam becomes a hit man in 1965 whose romance with the godfather's girlfriend places him in danger.
items.title: Double Identity

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S01E07 (The Color of Truth).mp4
items.summary: August 8, 1955: Sam experiences racism firsthand when he leaps into the body of an elderly black man in the pre-civil rights South of 1955.
items.title: The Color of Truth

items.summary: June 6, 1961: Sam leaps into the life of a teen-age hot-rodder who must stop his sister from marrying a wealthy bully.
items.title: Camikazi Kid

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S01E09 (Play It Again, Seymour).mp4
items.summary: April 14, 1953: With looks that could double for Humphrey Bogart, Sam is Nick Allen, a private investigator looking for the murderer of his partner and, if he doesn't find the answer in time, himself. The case is solved with a number of Casablanca references as Sam launches a new pulp novelist along the way.
items.title: Play it Again, Seymour

items.summary: April 27, 1960: As Tom McBride, a New York City cop on his honeymoon, Sam must save himself from a jealous, and sociopath, ex-husband. To make matters worse, the Project's funding will be cut off, stranding Sam alone in the past, unless he can prevent the U2 flight from being shot down over Russia.
items.title: Honeymoon Express

items.summary: April 1, 1976: As a stuntman, Sam is to save the life of his younger brother, while trying to convince the pair's obsessive father to let the younger son go his own way, even if it means going into country-western music, rather than following the family tradition of stunt work.
items.title: Disco Inferno

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S02E03 (The Americanization of Machiko).mp4
items.summary: August 4, 1953: As a sailor returning from Japan, Sam brings a foreign wife to a small town. He then has to fight against the prejudice of both a scheming ex-girlfriend, as well as his mother, in order to gain acceptance of his new bride.
items.title: The Americanization of Machiko

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S02E04 (What Price Gloria).mp4
items.summary: October 16, 1961: Sam is shocked when he learns he's leaped into a woman, Samantha Stormer. As a gorgeous secretary for an automobile company, Sam has to cope with sexual harassment by the boss, a suicide attempt by a roommate, and the effect his looks have on Al's lecherous tendencies.
items.title: What Price Gloria?

items.summary: February 6, 1964: Although the concert pianist he leaps into is blind, a fact, which bothers his girlfriend's disapproving mother, Sam can still see. At least until an exploding flashbulb blinds him at the crucial moment: when he must rescue his girlfriend from a serial killer.
items.title: Blind Faith

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S02E06 (Good Morning, Peoria).mp4
items.summary: September 9, 1959: Rock 'n' roll is about to become big, but not in Peoria. That is, unless Sam, as DJ Howlin' Chick Howell, can manage to keep the radio station where he's employed from being shut down by overly conservative town elders.
items.title: Good Morning, Peoria

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S02E07 (Thou Shalt Not...).mp4
items.summary: February 2, 1974: Sam's task as a rabbi is to keep his sister-in-law from falling for a sleazy author and ruining her life. In the process he also helps the family recover from the year-old death of their son.
items.title: Thou Shalt Not...

items.summary: October 14, 1964: Since mainstreaming the mentally ill is not yet a popular concept, Sam must help Jimmy LaMotta, the "slow" young man he's leaped into, get a job and gain his co-workers' acceptance, to prevent his brother from returning Jimmy to the institution.
items.title: Jimmy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S02E09 (So Help Me God).mp4
items.summary: July 29, 1957: Though he can't remember much more than habeas corpus, Sam finds himself the defense attorney for a young black woman accused of murdering the son of the most powerful man in a small Louisiana town.
items.title: So Help Me God

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S02E10 (Catch a Falling Star).mp4
items.summary: May 21, 1979: Sam leaps into Ray Hutton, the understudy for the role of Cervantes just seconds before curtain time. His mission: prevent the drunken star from falling and seriously injuring himself during a benefit performance of "Man of La Mancha." Sam isn't helped by the presence of his former piano teacher, on whom he once had a crush, and who now appears to have caught the star's eye as well.
items.title: Catch A Falling Star

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S02E11 (A Portrait for Troian).mp4
items.summary: February 7, 1971: Sam leaps into a renowned parapsychologist where he must prevent a young widow from joining her husband at the bottom of a lake, while proving that she's not crazy, despite her claims of hearing her dead husband calling to her.
items.title: A Portrait for Troian

items.summary: October 19, 1967: Trapped in the body of Knut Wileton, better known as "Wild Thing," the typical frat jock, Sam must win the confidence of an attractive campus radical before she bombs the college's chemistry building as a protest against the war in Vietnam.
items.title: Animal Frat

items.summary: September 30, 1981: As a divorced mother of three, Sam's job of preventing his teenage son from running away, never to be seen again, is made more interesting by the fact that his youngest daughter can see both him and Al.
items.title: Another Mother

items.summary: November 6, 1962: Keeping his best friend from throwing the high school championship football game, costing both of them their scholarship offers, Sam must also get their families to consolidate.
items.title: All-Americans

items.summary: September 26, 1973: Protecting a female member of the witness protection program from a mafia hitman proves difficult for Sam, since the FBI appears to have an informant confounding his attempts to hide her.
items.title: Her Charm

items.summary: November 22, 1970: Rather than saving his grandfather's life, Sam has to escape from jail and elude the police long enough to get them both to the reservation, where the old man can die in peace, at home.
items.title: Freedom

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S02E17 (Good Night Dear Heart).mp4
items.summary: November 9, 1957: Rather than saving the damsel of the episode, who supposedly committed suicide, Sam is the coroner trying to prove that she was murdered, and find out by whom.
items.title: Good Night, Dear Heart

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S02E18 (Pool Hall Blues).mp4
items.summary: September 4, 1954: In order to help his granddaughter save a small bar from the slimy loan shark holding a note on the place, Sam has to play pool like a pro...with a little help from Al and Ziggy.
items.title: Pool Hall Blues

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S02E19 (Leaping in Without a Net).mp4
items.summary: November 18, 1958: Sam remembers he's afraid of heights when he leaps into a trapeze artist, whose sister wants him to catch her as she does a triple without a net. Dad is less than pleased, since his wife died a few years earlier while attempting the same stunt.
items.title: Leaping in Without a Net

items.summary: March 11, 1963: Babysitting a kidnapped tot and a flaky, compulsively lying stripper keeps Sam busy as they cross Texas, on the run from the legal father and a squad of cops.
items.title: Maybe Baby

items.summary: June 3, 1954: Aboard an ocean liner, Sam must stop the marriage of a young man's ex-wife to a mobster. In the process, he finds himself in one heck of a mess in the ship's garbage compartment.
items.title: Sea Bride

items.summary: April 1, 1969: When Sam leaps into the life of an undercover cop, Al explains that his mission is to convince a navy nurse that her MIA husband is still alive, and to prevent her from marrying a lawyer she meets on the day Sam leaps in. But a series of coincidences causes Sam to wonder about the true nature of his mission.
items.title: M.I.A.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S03E01 (The Leap Home - Pt1).mp4
items.summary: November 25, 1969: As himself at the age of 16, Sam has the opportunity to both win the high school basketball championship and save his family from their sad fates.
items.title: The Leap Home (1)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S03E02 (The Leap Home - Pt2).mp4
items.summary: April 7, 1970: As a Navy SEAL in his own brother's squad, Sam must determine whether he is there to save Tom's life or ensure the success of the mission on which his brother was killed. Also Al from 1970 was a P.O.W.
items.title: The Leap Home (2): Vietnam

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S03E03 (Leap of Faith).mp4
items.summary: August 19, 1963: Sam finds himself in one holy mess as a priest in Philadelphia, trying to help an alcoholic priest deal with a killer and the death of a young parishioner.
items.title: Leap of Faith

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S03E04 (One Strobe over the Line).mp4
items.summary: June 15, 1965: Sam is a photographer who must protect a fashion model from a growing dependency on amphetamines and a predatory manager's ambitions.
items.title: One Strobe Over the Line

items.summary: October 31, 1964: Things do more than go bump in the night when Sam leaps into Joshua Raye, a horror novelist on Halloween. Although Ziggy claims he's there to prevent the death of a church deacon, things get even stranger when two more people die without warning.
items.title: The Boogieman

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S03E06 (Miss Deep South).mp4
items.summary: June 7, 1958: As Darlene Monte, a contestant in the "Miss Deep South" beauty pageant, Sam must come to the aid of an innocent contender who faces disgrace when she poses for naughty pictures taken by a sleazy pageant photographer. As if things weren't bad enough, Sam must ensure that Darlene finishes third, so that she'll go on to become a doctor.
items.title: Miss Deep South

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S03E07 (Black and White on Fire).mp4
items.summary: August 11, 1965: Sam leaps into a black med. student engaged to a white woman in order to ensure that he and his fiancée survive the Watts Riot together.
items.title: Black on White on Fire

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S03E08 (The Great Spontini).mp4
items.summary: May 9, 1974: Leaping into magician Harry Spontini, Sam has to prevent his estranged wife from taking their daughter away from him as she files for divorce, so she can marry her sleazy divorce attorney.
items.title: The Great Spontini

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S03E09 (Rebel without a Clue).mp4
items.summary: September 1, 1958: As "Bones," a member of a motorcycle gang, Sam is an uneasy rider who has to prevent a Jack Kerouac-inspired young woman from meeting her death on the road.
items.title: Rebel without a Clue

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S03E10 (A Little Miracle).mp4
items.summary: December 24, 1962: On Christmas Eve, Sam leap into Reginald Pierson, valet to a wealthy contractor, who is in danger of losing his soul in an attempt to demolish a Salvation Army mission, so he can build his "Blake's Plaza." Seeing a similarity to the Dickens's character, Sam and Al decide to "Scrooge" the greed out of the man.
items.title: A Little Miracle

items.summary: July 4, 1964: On a cross-country car trip, Sam, as 13-year-old Butchie, must contend with a sadistic older sister and a mother on the verge of running away from an unfulfilling marriage, in search of the feminine mystique.
items.title: Runaway

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S03E12 (Eight and a Half Months).mp4
items.summary: November 15, 1955: Billie Jean Crockett is a pregnant teenager who will make the second biggest mistake of her life - giving her baby up for adoption - unless Sam, as Billie Jean, can convince someone to help her raise her child... before he goes into labor himself
items.title: 8½ Months

items.summary: October 6, 1957: Sam leaps Kenny Sharp, better known as "Future Boy," sidekick to Moe Stein, host of the kid's show, "Time Patrol," who also happens to be building a time machine in his basement. Unless Sam can prevent Moe's daughter from attempting to have her father committed, Moe is destined to be killed as he tries to hop a freight train.
items.title: Future Boy

items.summary: October 6, 1979: An aspiring dancer working as a waitress in a strip club is in danger of being led into a life of prostitution unless Sam, as "Rod the Bod," can convince her to audition for a spot in a professional dance group. But, since she's deaf, the choreographer doesn't believe she has the time to give the young lady the attention she'll need.
items.title: Private Dancer

items.summary: November 10, 1985: Joey Dinardo is a lounge lizard on the run from mob hitmen. When Sam leaps in, his ex-girlfriend, and former musical partner have found him, and now both are on a run for their lives from a killer who seems to know their every move.
items.title: Piano Man

items.summary: August 4, 1961: It's the best little cathouse in New Orleans. No, it's the Gilbert Labonte Sewin' & Quiltin' Academy. As the proprietor of this worthy establishment, Sam must prevent the mysterious death of a resident who doesn't belong there.
items.title: Southern Comforts

items.summary: April 12, 1974: Sam is a glitter rock star in danger of being stabbed to death after a performance, unless Sam can determine who, from a growing list of people, the real killer is.
items.title: Glitter Rock

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S03E18 (A Hunting We Will Go).mp4
items.summary: June 18, 1976: It's the leap from hell as Sam, a bounty hunter handcuffed to a wily embezzler who will stop at nothing to get away from him, has to deal with his captive, as well as his attraction towards her, despite her countless attacks on him.
items.title: A Hunting We Will Go

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S03E19 (Last Dance Before Execution).mp4
items.summary: May 12, 1971: "Just think of someplace far away" is the advice Sam hears as he leaps into Jesus Ortega, a Cuban-American being strapped into an electric chair. A last second stay of execution gives Sam just forty-eight hours to either prove himself innocent or fulfill his mission so that he can leap before the Big Switch is pulled
items.title: Last Dance Before an Execution

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S03E20 (Heart of a Champion).mp4
items.summary: July 23, 1955: The heart of a champion belongs to Ronnie, a professional wrestler, who will die if he competes in the title match. Sam, as his brother and new partner Terry, must convince him of his hidden health problem, while avoiding his own health problem - the jealous wrestler-husband of a woman who has taken an amorous interest in Sam.
items.title: Heart of a Champion

items.summary: October 26, 1962: Sam finds himself the brother of a fallout shelter salesman during the Cuban Missile Crisis, where he must defuse a potentially explosive situation as panic sets in on the night of John F. Kennedy's speech to the nation.
items.title: Nuclear Family

items.summary: October 3, 1954: Leaping into Sam Bederman, a mental patient who is suffering from acute depression, Sam receives an overloaded electroshock treatment, which causes his Swiss-cheesed memory to be replaced by personas from previous leaps. Al, finding himself visible to the mentally absent, must try to complete Sam's mission, and convince him to take another shock treatment, in order to leap Sam out before contact is lost forever.
items.title: Shock Theater

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S04E01 (The Leap Back).mp4
items.summary: June 15, 1945: Struck by lightning, Sam and Al find their roles reversed, as Sam returns to the future, and to a long-lost love, while Al leaps back to 1945 to prevent the death of a returning World War II hero and his former girl friend.
items.title: The Leap Back

items.summary: August 6, 1961: A pitcher on a minor league baseball team, Sam must decide if he's there to help a fellow team member, get his host back into the major leagues, or baby-sit the porcine team mascot, all while resisting the amorous advances of the women in his life.
items.title: Play Ball

items.summary: August 17, 1969: Sam meets Camille, and possibly a killer, when he leaps into a deputy sheriff in a small Mississippi town, lying in the path of a deadly hurricane.
items.title: Hurricane

items.summary: May 11, 1965: Sam must don the robe of a Ku Klux Klansman in order to save the life of an ambitious young civil rights leader, who is trying to register black voters.
items.title: Justice

items.summary: June 2, 1983: Sam leaps into Frank Bianca, a hairstylist in leather pants, to prevent the death of a young murder witness and his mother.
items.title: Permanent Wave

items.summary: June 20, 1980: It's up to Sam to try to bring a rapist to justice when he leaps into the perp's victim, a young woman who may have been unwilling to press charges against the young man - the son of the pillar of the community.
items.title: Raped

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S04E07 (The Wrong Stuff).mp4
items.summary: January 24, 1961: The fates make a monkey out of Sam when he leaps into Bobo, an astro-chimp who must avoid succumbing to the experiments of an Air Force neurologist.
items.title: The Wrong Stuff

items.summary: February 28, 1979: It's more like a nightmare when Sam leaps into a detective, investigating a gruesome murder. He may be next if he doesn't find out who eviscerated the victim and his only hope is the victim's catatonic son and her husband's psychiatrist. The horrific flashbacks he's experiencing don't help matters much either.
items.title: Dreams

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S04E09 (A Single Drop of Rain).mp4
items.summary: September 7, 1953: A devastating drought will be the ruin of a small town unless Sam, as Billy Beaumont, "purveyor of precipitation and maker of rain," can find a way to make it rain, while keeping his family together in the process.
items.title: A Single Drop of Rain

items.summary: November 2, 1956: Sam and a fellow convict named Boone are the defiant ones when Sam has to rescue his companion from a fifteen-year sentence on a chain gang.
items.title: Unchained

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S04E11 (The Play's the Thing).mp4
items.summary: September 9, 1969: May meets December when Sam leaps into a young actor in love with an older woman, who is also an aspiring singer. If he can't boost her confidence and help her get her career on track, she will face a "fate worse than death," returning with her son to Cleveland.
items.title: The Play's the Thing

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S04E12 (Running for Honor).mp4
items.summary: June 11, 1964: As a track star in a Navy college, Sam must prevent the death of his ex- roommate, who was expelled because he was gay, and who is slated to die at the hands of a group of bigoted cadets.
items.title: Running for Honor

items.summary: February 1, 1985: A serial killer stalks San Francisco while Sam as Dillion Powell, a TV reporter, protects a beautiful psychic who's working on the case, from becoming the next victim. The young lady is very clear of sight, as Sam and Al soon discover.
items.title: Temptation Eyes

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S04E14 (The Last Gunfighter).mp4
items.summary: November 28, 1957: Sam finds himself in the life of Tyler Meanes, a teller of tall tales who faces death at the hand of an old friend in a shootout at high noon.
items.title: The Last Gunfighter

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S04E15 (A Song for the Soul).mp4
items.summary: April 7, 1963: As a backup singer in a black, amateur girl group Sam finds between the fifteen year-old lead singer and her father as he attempts to rescue the girl from a sleazy night club owner's clutches.
items.title: A Song for the Soul

items.summary: August 13, 1956: Flying over the Bermuda Triangle, Sam, as the co-pilot, must prevent the flight from returning to Virginia, to get a seriously ill passenger to a doctor before she dies. Flying through the triangle is riskier than it seems, and Sam, deprived of Al's help when the hologram fades out, must get them through alive.
items.title: Ghost Ship

items.summary: January 27, 1982: Sam, as "Roberto!" is a tabloid talk show host a la Geraldo who, with an asthmatic rival and co-worker, tries to uncover a mystery at a local chemical plant, a mystery, which may prove to be deadly for his co-worker.
items.title: Roberto!

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S04E18 (It's a Wonderful Life).mp4
items.summary: May 10, 1958: Sam finds himself behind the wheel of a New York taxicab, in the life of Max Greenman, a driver striving to win his own tag, a license to drive his own cab. His mission is aided with the help of a woman who claims to be a guardian angel.
items.title: It's A Wonderful Leap

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S04E19 (Moments to Live).mp4
items.summary: May 4, 1985: Sam is a soap opera heart surgeon and the obsession of a love-struck, if somewhat deranged fan. He must escape from the woman and her husband who kidnap him for reproductive purposes
items.title: Moments to Live

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S04E20 (The Curse of Ptah-Hotep).mp4
items.summary: March 2, 1957: It's almost as though Sam were on vacation when, as Egyptologist Dale Conway, he gets to read hieroglyphics, search lost tombs, and, of course, visit Egypt. But between an encroaching sandstorm, computer glitches back at the Project, the suspicious deaths of the guides, and a 3000-year-old curse to round things off, Sam has very little time to play in the sand.
items.title: The Curse of Ptah-Hotep

items.summary: April 30, 1959: Sam, as the singing half of a comedy team, soon finds that trying to convince two people that they're truly in love is no laughing matter, especially when one of them is the object of a sleazy casino owner's desire.
items.title: Stand Up

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S04E22 (Leap for Lisa).mp4
items.summary: June 25, 1957: Sam leaps into Al Calavicci to prevent the death of his married lover. But when Sam accidentally alters history, and finds out too late about her untimely demise, it could mean the gas chamber for Al and disturbingly a whole new situation at Project Quantum Leap.
items.title: A Leap for Lisa

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S05E01, E02 (Lee Harvey Oswald).mp4
items.summary: October 5, 1957 - November 22, 1963: As a result of leaping again before he had a chance to complete his original mission, Sam finds himself leaping back and forth through the life of Lee Harvey Oswald. Following the sole assassin theory, Sam and Al attempt to prevent Oswald's attack on John F. Kennedy. But, with each leap giving Oswald more control over Sam's body, history seems doomed to repeat itself.
items.title: Lee Harvey Oswald (1)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S05E03 (Leaping of the Shrew).mp4
items.summary: September 27, 1956: It's Robinson Crusoe with a twist when Sam leaps into a Greek sailor stranded on a deserted island with a beautiful young rich woman who appears to be less than fond of both him and their stranded situation.
items.title: Leaping of the Shrew

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S05E04 (Nowhere to Run).mp4
items.summary: August 10, 1968: As a Marine captain whose legs were amputated after a mishap in Vietnam, Sam finds himself in a veteran's hospital, where he must prevent the suicide of a fellow patient who would rather be dead than face life paralyzed from the neck down. Making matters worse, his wife seems incapable of accepting the fact that she and Sam's host can still lead a normal life, in spite of his condition.
items.title: Nowhere to Run

items.summary: June 18, 1958: Sam leaps into a tricky situation as an escaped killer holed up in a house with a mother and daughter as hostages. Escape isn't going to be easy for either Sam or his hostages, when the real killer breaks out of the waiting room, stranding Sam in the past, destined to die at the hands of a vengeful sheriff.
items.title: Killin' Time

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S05E06 (Star Light, Star Bright).mp4
items.summary: May 21, 1966: Sam leaps into a 79-year-old man whose son wants to have him committed when he claims to have seen UFO's. Sam is kept busy as he tries to keep the family together, prevent the future drug overdose of "his" grandson, and avoid the sinister plans of the military, all before the next anticipated UFO sighting.
items.title: Star Light, Star Bright

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S05E07 (Deliver Us From Evil).mp4
items.summary: March 19, 1966: Things are already on there way downhill when Sam leaps back into Jimmy LaMotta. Despite Sam's inaction, history continues to change for the worst. The cause is unknown until Sam discovers another time traveler on the scene, one who's determined to destroy Jimmy's family, as well as Sam.
items.title: Deliver Us from Evil

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S05E08 (One Little Heart - 1of3).mp4
items.summary: August 8, 1955: A pair of unsolved murders marks just the tip of the iceberg when Sam leaps into a sheriff in a small Louisiana town. Rumors of a history of family insanity, the suspicions surrounding his daughter Abigail's involvement in the murders, and ghostly visions of his institutionalized wife just make matters worse.
items.title: Trilogy (1)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S05E09 (For Your Love - 2of3).mp4
items.summary: June 14, 1966: Finding himself back in the same small Louisiana town, in the arms of Abigail, now twenty-one, Sam must prevent an angry crowd of townspeople from lynching his fiancée, following the disappearance of a young boy whom she had been babysitting.
items.title: Trilogy (2)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S05E10 (The Last Door - 3of3).mp4
items.summary: July 28, 1978: Sam is an aging lawyer, recruited by Abigail, now thirty-three, to defend her when she is put on trial for the murder of Leta Aider, the woman whose daughter Abigail was accused of killing almost twenty-five years earlier.
items.title: Trilogy (3)

items.summary: December 22, 1971: Sam leaps back to Elk Ridge, Indiana to help save the lives of the Walters boys as they try to save their farm from a banker with designs on getting rich from foreclosure.
items.title: Promised Land

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S05E12 (Tale of Two Sweeties).mp4
items.summary: February 25, 1958: As a horse-playing, traveling brush salesman, Sam finds himself with two wives and two families. Although Ziggy predicts that Sam's mission is to choose between the two lives, the choice is made more difficult by the fact that there's only a 50/50 chance that he'll choose the right one. As if things weren't bad enough, Sam finds that his penniless host owes a pair of bookies some big bucks.
items.title: A Tale of Two Sweeties

items.summary: October 16, 1968: Leaping into a housewife and mother of two on the verge of women's lib, Sam must prevent the death of his daughter during a sit in, while convincing the girl's father that his marriage can survive a liberated wife and daughter.
items.title: Liberation

items.summary: April 25, 1985: While Sam is in 1985, running her radio talk show, playing matchmaker to her producers, and trying to help a young secretary who's being sexually harassed by her boss, Dr. Ruth Westheimer spends her time in the Waiting Room, counseling Al on his feelings towards his five wives, as well as his relationship with Tina.
items.title: Dr. Ruth

items.summary: March 10, 1975: As an eccentric, possibly vampiric, artist just outside of London, Sam must bear with Al's superstitions, while trying to prevent the death of his host's young wife, at the hands of a couple who are taking a sacrificial ceremony in honor of the "blood moon."
items.title: Blood Moon

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S05E16 (Return of the Evil Leaper).mp4
items.summary: October 8, 1956: As Arnold Watkins, better known as The Midnight Marauder, Sam has to persuade a fraternity to stop using chicken races as a part of their hazing ceremonies, while Al tries to convince Arnold to stop trying to get himself killed in retaliation for his parents' deaths twelve years earlier. When Alia, the evil leaper, appears on the scene, Sam becomes determined to take her with him when he leaps.
items.title: Return of the Evil Leaper (1)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S05E17 (Revenge of the Evil Leaper).mp4
items.summary: September 16, 1987: Having simu-leaped, both Sam and Alia find themselves trapped in a women's prison, accused of murdering a fellow inmate. Their efforts to unmask the real killer are not their top priority as the two attempt to keep Alia's location hidden from her observer, Zoey, who leaps into the same place and time, determined to make Alia pay for her betrayal.
items.title: Revenge of the Evil Leaper (2)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S05E18 (Goodbye Norma Jean).mp4
items.summary: April 4, 1960: As chauffeur to Marilyn Monroe, Sam must try to prevent Marilyn's tragic death. But when a well-meaning plan backfires, it could mean the end of Marilyn's career, even if her life is saved.
items.title: Goodbye Norma Jean

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S05E19 (The Beast Within).mp4
items.summary: November 6, 1972: Sam leaps into Henry Adams, one of a trio of friends who fought in Vietnam and came home each with their own personal scars and the memory of a lost buddy. He has to save the life of a friend, Roy, as well as of a young boy, Daniel, who ventures into the woods of Washington looking for proof of Bigfoot.
items.title: The Beast Within

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Quantum Leap/Quantum Leap S05E20 (The Leap Between the States).mp4
items.summary: September 20, 1862: In a bizarre twist of a genetic coil, Sam leaps into his great-grandfather, Captain John Beckett, during the Civil War. He must not interfere with his ancestor's romance with a riled southern belle named Olivia. He must also avoid being hanged as a Yankee dog by some home guard Confederate soldiers.
items.title: The Leap Between the States

items.summary: July 3, 1954: Sam swivels his hips into Elvis Presley, mere days before he is discovered. Along with making sure that Elvis does become the King, Sam must help Sue Anne, a local songbird, from being trapped in a not-so-gilded cage of marriage.
items.title: Memphis Melody

items.summary: August 8, 1953: Sam lands in a not-so-ordinary bar in a coal-mining town, where strange things are happening and familiar people don't know him. With the help of another Al, he still has something to set right ... or is there more than one thing he needs to change?
items.title: Mirror Image
